properties.nom_etablissement: % Arabica Marrakech ciguë
properties.adresse: Local L07, M Avenue, Marrakesh 40020, Maroc
properties.description_projet:
After their first address at Dumbo NewYork, % Arabica is opening a store on the new Avenue M in a fashionable neighbourhood of Marrakech. ciguë runs the codes of the Japanese brand— huge windows looking out onto Avenue M, open space, long benches and counters— through the filter of the cultural and architectural codes typical of Marrakech. The sleek design and materials for the seats and counter made of pisé draw their inspiration from the ruins of the 16th-century Saadien El Badi Palace, an indoor fountain tiled with zellige from Fès cools the air, and traditional bejmat enamel tiles cover the floors. ciguë distils the codes of % arabica in Marrakech: Chemex glass jars are arranged in a cascade to feed the fountain, while the minimalism typical of ciguë and Japan can be found in the brass feet of the tables, the delicate shelving and the windows opening onto the roasting area and Avenue M.

Main materials: 

Seats and counter: compressed raw earth (pisé), corian and cast concrete

Floor: enamelled bejmat tiles

Pool: enamelled zellige tiles

Fountain: stainless steel tubing

Jars: Chemex glass.

properties.nom_etablissement: AW² , Shirvan Métisse Doha, 7 La Croisette, Porto Arabia Drive, Doha, Qatar
properties.adresse: 7 La Croisette, Porto Arabia Drive, Doha, Qatar
properties.description_projet: Shirvan Métisse Doha is located in the prominent Pearl Marina, amidst high-end shops and restaurants aimed at local Qataris and tourists. The 600sqm, 140-person capacity restaurant sits across two floors and includes a lounge area and bar, a large dining hall and expansive terraced areas for diners to enjoy views across the marina and the Doha skyline. Shirvan Métisse Doha has been designed to simulate a journey on the Silk Route, through the culinary traditions of the various countries that are encountered. AW2 used textures, colours, materials and lighting to create a series of different atmospheres to give guests the sense of moving through various environments as they experience the different spaces in the restaurant. At the entrance to the restaurant, a brass lattice screen, resembling a traditional mashrabiyya, combined with dimmed and indirect lighting creates a sense of privacy. Intricate lattice screens continue to feature on the internal walls, aiming to direct guests towards the main dining hall or the mezzanine lounge and bar on the top floor. Elemental materials including timber, bronze, marble and leather are used throughout. The central space of the restaurant is octagonal and double-height. It features a show kitchen allowing guests to see Benallal’s team at work. Olive trees and spices displayed on a marble table recall the colourful food markets of the region. Arched floor-to-ceiling windows open towards the marina where additional outdoor seating is provided. Outdoor dining areas are shaded by wooden pergolas and olive trees. The furniture has been bespoke designed by AW2. The black granite floor contrasts with grey marbles and brass inserts in the tables. Bold ornamental elements such as mesh pendant lights along with an openwork brass Yemeni pattern cover the ceiling and create a play of light and shadows throughout. Alternated carved wooden panels and mineral rendered walls enclose the space and reflect the light across the room. Reda Amalou & Stéphanie Ledoux, Partners at AW² commented: “Shirvan Restaurant is an insightful study of experiential space design in which the architecture and the interiors aim to enhance the sensorial experience already provided by chef Akrame Benallal’s phenomenal cuisine. It creates a place for people to absorb Qatar’s culture, intertwining tradition with contemporary design.” ©Architect: AW² - Reda Amalou & Stéphanie Ledoux

properties.nom_etablissement: Humbert & Poyet, Florida, Monte-Carlo, Monaco
properties.description_projet: We designed a great duplex in Monaco, the interior of which became the backdrop for the luxury art collection. We had a beautiful carte blanche. The only guidelines: a contemporary flat in H&I style. That it be a family flat as well as a reception flat. A project that works on the enhancement of the owners' art collection. Our main starting point of the design of this duplex was the owners extensive and diverse collection of art. We wanted to balance the playful and bold elements of their collection with a soft and neutral palette to subtly draw the eye to the artworks while maintaining a contemporary yet sophisticated mood. In order to highlight the works, we installed many custom finishes, designing new patterns and mouldings in the process. For example, in the living room we created a freestanding L-shaped shelving unit in front of the windows to display the owner’s eclectic collection of smaller sculptural pieces while allowing for the natural light to pass into the space. A real game between our architecture and their collection. The collectors chose the pieces according to the designed space. It was quite playful because everything was not defined in advance. It was like a journey of sensitivity between interior design and art. A real dialogue to highlight both.

properties.nom_etablissement: ciguë, Genesis Studio , Genesis, G-030/287 Lonsdale St, Melbourne VIC 3000, Australie
properties.adresse: Genesis, G-030/287 Lonsdale St, Melbourne VIC 3000, Australie
properties.description_projet: For the first showroom devoted to the high-end car brand Genesis in Melbourne, Ciguë explores new frontiers. First there’s a lounge fitted out in genuine wood and leather; its sleek lines, inspired by American case study houses, are a nod to the neo-rural minimalism of Australian architect Glenn Murcutt. Then we have the showroom itself, a dematerialised fictional world turned white by fantasies speed and in-car tech. The design treads a fine line between rootedness and escapism, awareness and excitement, while remaining in full control of resources, time and space. A new way of experiencing mobility!

Brother of balagan restaurant in Paris, we have reused some of its codes : tiles handmade in the south of Italy, neon light, lava from Auvergne… but we have also created new codes inspired by Ibiza bohemia. properties.nom_etablissement: Wilmotte & Associés, House of UNO in Senegal, Diamniadio, Senegal
properties.description_projet: The House of UNO is an outstanding project located in the new incoming ministries district Diamniadio, nearby Dakar, in Senegal. Initiated by the Senegalese government, the challenge consisted of gathering the 34 UN agencies scattered in Dakar in a new iconic and radiant building. Its shape reminds a water mill or a sun which rays evoke concentration but also radiation and influences. It appears as a white circular volume with seven radiant wings. The spatial conception leads to a strong identity: the combination of independence and collaboration for the agencies in its inside and the symbol of a powerful decision center in a brand-new urban landscape. The landscape on the surrounding will assure the link between this not so common shape and the urban plan. By the uses of local material for grounds and vegetation, the garden will create the link between the local soil and the international sphere. In its conception, its construction and future running the House of UNO as a public building will promote exemplarity in terms of energy and accessibility. The spatial modulation of the program echoes with the shape : The official spaces will be situated in the very heart of the edifice: amphitheater and reception spaces will host international conferences, seminaries and debates. This central activity will be sustained by a ring of public and common spaces such as informatic support, consultation centers, meeting points, restauration areas and so on. Connected to the shared circle, the agencies, action forces of UN, will take place in the rays, as a symbol of spreading UNO’s values.

properties.description_projet: Tashkent Center for Islamic Civilization is a flagship project for the Republic of Uzbekistan. It hosts an academy, a conference hall, a library, a museum and the national archives. Old manuscripts, lithographic books, historical documents will be kept there. This place will also highlight modern research studies carried out by great scientists and religious figures who lived in the territory of modern Uzbekistan. The main relic of the Center will be the Samarkand Kufic Koran, also known as the Usman Koran, dating from the late 7th and early 8th centuries.

properties.adresse: 114, 1 Naradhiwas Rajanagarindra Rd, Silom, Bang Rak, Bangkok 10500, Thaïlande
properties.description_projet: Escape to Bangkok’s new signature dining destination and sky-high oasis with a world-class chef and exhilarating views BANGKOK- Mahanakhon Bangkok SkyBar, Thailand’s highest restaurant and bar is open at Bangkok’s landmark destination, King Power Mahanakhon. Located in the heart of Sathorn and directly connected to Chong Nonsi BTS station, the new dining venue is situated on the 76th and 77th floor of the iconic pixelated building. Inspired by the Chaopraya river and the concept of an eclectic journey, a visit to the upscale modern brasserie allows one to step into an exotic escape from the usual hustle and bustle of Bangkok. Tastefully designed indoor and outdoor seating areas, along with exclusive VIP lounges offer a comfortable dining venue for guests to enjoy world-class mixology and unique dishes. Interior masterpiece led by Tristan Auer, Mahanakhon Bangkok SkyBar is Bangkok’s newest iconic dining destination.

properties.nom_etablissement: Studio Adrien Gardère, Tarrkarri, Adelaide, Australie
properties.description_projet: Diller Scofidio + Renfro (DS+R) and Woods Bagot, with Studio Adrien Gardere, in charge of museography and design, were appointed for Adelaide Contemporary - renamed Tarrkarri - Centre for first nations culture - international design competition organized by Arts South Australia and Malcolm Reading Consultants. Tarrkarri is a new museum showcasing the past, present and future of Aboriginal culture and its artistic practices across all disciplines. The design of the building stems from the Aboriginal conception of the elements that connect us to a place: earth, land and sky. Lower level galleries and terraced landscapes are carved into the earth, providing indoor exhibition spaces that integrate the museum's visible, accessible and dynamic reserves with the performance spaces and space dedicated to traditional Aboriginal welcome ceremonies. The upper galleries break western conventions by introducing exhibition spaces that vary in size, height and light, and offer unique views of the sky, the natural environment and Aboriginal culture.

properties.nom_etablissement: Studio Adrien Gardère, Gozo Museum, Gozo, Malte
properties.description_projet: In 2016, NIDUM Architects — founded by Christopher Micallef together with Michael Pace, Joanna Spiteri Staines and Alberto Miceli-Farrugia — won the competition for the Gozo Museum in the island capital Victoria (Gozo - Malta). In 2018, NIDUM called upon Studio Adrien Gardère to join their team as lead museographer, exhibition designer and artistic consultant. The new museum comprises the extension and rehabilitation of the Ninu Cremona Boys Lyceum, an iconic piece of modernist architecture designed in the 1950s by architect Joseph Huntingford. In 2019, the discovery of an extensive ancient quarry, dating back to the Punic and Roman periods on the site, brought the whole team to reinvent its project around the “sea of stone” that surrounds the modernist building and to create a completely new scheme and journey through the history and narratives that have defined the Gozitan identity.

properties.nom_etablissement: Studio Adrien Gardère, Musée de Tahiti, Punaauia, Polynésie Française
properties.description_projet: Studio Adrien Gardère, in collaboration with Pierre-Jean Picart , architect, won the competition in 2016 to design the renovation and the extension of the Museum of Tahiti and her islands - Te Fare Manaha. This transformation and extension of the exhibition spaces offer a unique and new perspective on Polynesian art and culture to the public. The museum complex aims to be a place of encounter with a cultural heritage and its historical, scientific, artistic, identity and pedagogical stakes. The museography deploys a contemporary approach breaking with the traditional standards of scenography, inscribingthe project'scapacity for evolution at the heart of the project by removing all partitions. To refer to the wide geographical and cultural areas of Polynesia, the scenography develops itself in archipelagos, island activating themes and sequences. The scenography allows a better understanding of the five main Polynesian archipelagos, their connections and cultural characteristics along with influences of the contacts with occidental societies.

properties.nom_etablissement: Studio Adrien Gardère, PHOTO ELYSEE, Place de la Gare 17, 1003 Lausanne, Suisse
properties.adresse: Place de la Gare 17, 1003 Lausanne, Suisse
properties.description_projet: The PHOTO ELYSEE has entrusted Studio Adrien Gardère with the design and artistic direction of all its exhibition and mediation spaces as part of the Museum's move to its new building designed by the architects Aires Matteus in the heart of the PLATEFORME 10 arts district. The COLLECTIONS space, "60 species of photographic spaces", responds to PHOTO ELYSEE's desire to reinterpret one of the classic museographic formats, namely the presentation of collections, in a dynamic, stimulating and contemporary way. The exhibition system designed by Studio Adrien Gardère, composed of a set of mobile, modular and reconfigurable trolleys, constitutes a real exhibition and hanging tool for the collections. It allows the immense thematic diversity of the collections to be mapped. The STUDIO space, designed with the multimedia agency on-situ, engages the public in the participatory discovery of photographic practice through a series of immersive, interactive and playful experiences. Staging, rayograms, studio photography and editing are part of this new experience of the creation of a photograph by the public.

properties.description_projet: ART DE VIVRE supports the interior architects and designers in their most demanding projects thanks to the exclusive line of furniture, made to measure designed by Bruno Moinard and thanks to the expertise of the most talented French craftsmen that it represents. Some pieces of furniture are visible in our Abu Dhabi office.

properties.nom_etablissement: Jouin Manku , La Maison Van Cleef & Arpels' Seoul , Van Cleef & Arpels' Maison Seoul, 441, Apgujeong-ro, Gangnam-gu, Séoul, Corée du Sud
properties.titre_affiche: La Maison Van Cleef & Arpels Seoul
properties.adresse: Van Cleef & Arpels Maison Seoul, 441, Apgujeong-ro, Gangnam-gu, Séoul, Corée du Sud
properties.description_projet: "A Maison Jardin" After Paris, New York, Hong Kong and Tokyo, the Jouin Manku studio has completed Van Cleef & Arpels’ maison in Seoul. For this new project, Patrick Jouin and Sanjit Manku were entrusted with the entire architectural conception of the building, the interior architecture and the design of every final detail. A complete project and a new opportunity to share a fascination for the world, as the studio celebrates its sixteenth year of collaboration with the exceptional French maison de haute joaillerie. Van Cleef & Arpels is driven by savoir-faire and a demand for excellence, but also by culture and heritage, and continues to play an important role in the development of the decorative arts. Under the management of Nicolas Bos, we see a brand that is heavily involved in a range of cultural activities, from commissioning dance performances to sponsoring a school of jewellery arts. It is this commitment that has fuelled the Jouin Manku studio. These cultural alliances are interwoven throughout Van Cleef & Arpels’ commercial activity, ensuring the company’s status as a powerful purveyor of dreams. This project seeks to offer Korea a Van Cleef & Arpels showcase, exposing its level of craftsmanship, its heritage and taste for the arts and culture, as well as expressing the links between the east and the west, embracing and celebrating Korean culture. No question of bringing in ideas of style, but rather of teasing out a sophisticated blend, inextricably combining commerce and culture, contemporary and craftsmanship. Jouin Manku has put its vision of European and occidental architecture to the test by endeavouring to embrace Korean ideas, reflecting the country’s vast cultural wealth in the project. Advocating the spirit of opening up to the world in order to find our natural place in a new ecosystem. “With the creation of this new Maison, we are celebrating ever stronger bonds with this country, known for a long tradition of craftsmanship that echoes the values espoused by Van Cleef & Arpels. Indeed, the boutique was designed to form a union between the French jewelry tradition and Korean cultural heritage, and to nurture this dialogue for years to come.” Nicolas Bos- President and CEO of Van Cleef & Arpels “This project offered us the opportunity to imagine a whole new building, a structure that would establish Van Cleef & Arpels as a prominent feature in the Seoul landscape. Over five levels, we designed a dreamlike natural decor with spaces suited to hosting artistic functions – exhibitions and conferences – along an itinerary in which lively spaces alternate with intimate islands of tranquility.” Sanjit Manku & Patrick Jouin - Studio Jouin Manku

properties.nom_etablissement: Humbert & Poyet, Grand Jusan Jeju, Grand Jusan Jeju, 60 Jungmungwangwang-ro72beon-gil, Seogwipo-si, Jeju-do, Corée du Sud
properties.adresse: Grand Jusan Jeju, 60 Jungmungwangwang-ro72beon-gil, Seogwipo-si, Jeju-do, Corée du Sud
properties.description_projet: The Grand Josun Jeju is designed to reflect its rich natural environment, full of life, texture and serenity. A space of refuge and tranquility where one connects to nature and its elements. Each room is designed to reflect Jeju, with the use of natural raw materials, volcanic stone, rattan, fibers, concrete and rich marble and terrazzo. The color palette is earth toned, warm sandstone colors, emerald greens and ocean blues. Arches and open perspectives are designed for natural light. Organic shapes and patterns decorate the space.

properties.nom_etablissement: Humbert & Poyet, Grand Jusan Busan, Grand Jusan Busan, 292 Haeundaehaebyeon-ro, Haeundae-gu, Busan, Corée du Sud
properties.adresse: Grand Jusan Busan, 292 Haeundaehaebyeon-ro, Haeundae-gu, Busan, Corée du Sud
properties.description_projet:
An environment inspired by nature, warm and balanced. A mix of modern and classic, graphic and understated sophistication. Rich materials are used, marble, terrazzo, wood, velvets, metals,

with texture, creating an environment that is alive, elegant and joyous, signed with the colors of the sea and earth, framed in black. The curves and femininity of nature are balanced with the masculine lines of urbanism. Signed with terracota, rose, juniper green, sandstone, safran and ocean blues. Each space is inviting and an experience in its own offering the guest the sensation of walking through an ocean estate.

properties.nom_etablissement: Jouin Manku , La Mamounia , Avenue Bab Jdid، Marrakesh 40040, Maroc
properties.description_projet: The first time we visited La Mamounia, we had that strange and comforting sensation of time slowing down, of life becoming simpler. Keeping hold of that feeling, we walked around the different spaces, breathing in their potential. Staying at La Mamounia should be a succession of unique experiences, with the different restaurants being the main player in promoting this adventure. Both the Italian and Asian restaurants, under the management of Jean-Georges Vongerichten have been transformed. After rethinking the restaurants, we turned our minds to surprises for the guests. The first one is Pierre Hermé's salon de thé, designed around the principles of Moroccan tearooms with their banquettes facing one another along the walls. The water reflects a huge glass chandelier. The Churchill Bar, the cinema, the pool bar, the oenothèque, the pool pavilion, and the Moroccan bar are added to the list of spaces reinvented by the agency and each of them has its personality. The lanterns and the wine bar are probably the most spectacular concept, in the middle of the lush greenery, three large lanterns which house a wine bar and two private lounges. A way to breathe energy into this part which once formed a sort of barrier between the hotel and the swimming pool, but also the possibility of creating a warm place through the woodwork.

properties.nom_etablissement: ELLE INTERIOR STORIES, Cocottes Infinity, INFINITY Shopping Center, Av. John F. Kennedy, 1499 Luxembourg
properties.adresse: INFINITY Shopping Center, Av. John F. Kennedy, 1499 Luxembourg
properties.description_projet: The challenge for EL'LE Interior stories architects was to allow the various restaurants to meet strict Integration criteria according to the city districts In which they were located. The target with Infinity was to energize a new district and be a meeting place for the people working In the area.

properties.nom_etablissement: ELLE INTERIOR STORIES, Casino 2000, 5 Rue Flammang, 5618 Mondorf-les-Bains, Luxembourg
properties.description_projet: The "Boutique", in the middle of the slot machines area , offers an incomparable moment of relaxation. Inspired by the circus atmosphere, you can take a break and chat for a while over a drink or a delicious snack. The challenge was to completely transform this area while allowing it to continue to integrate perfectly with the old identity of the place. The gastronomic restaurant "Les Roses" has been redesigned to be more elegant and modern. The interior architecture has been designed to support the sober and modern cuisine of its new Chef, and the colors and materials have been chosen to match the aesthetics of the dishes. The "Dome", with its specific ventilation system, features a circulation area for smokers and is adorned with materials that are at once eco-responsible, sober and practical. The "Manège" has a resolutely upscale identity that creates a world distinct from the rest of the Casino, and houses the gaming tables and a cocktail bar with V.I.P. accents.

properties.nom_etablissement: KNGB, ZX living store, Taipei, Taiwan
properties.description_projet: Our collaboration with Zx living started following their 1st participation in Maison et Objet in 2018. We made floor lamps in natural oak and light grey fabrics to meet the Taiwanese demand. We use subtle elegance to illuminate home and building interiors with our range of high-end lighting solutions. KNGB's lampshades are handcrafted in our workshop and the various stands and lighting accessories are made from premium raw materials including oak, vegetable-tanned leather, metal and wool flannel - all sourced locally from the best artisans and producers in the region. This is what seduced the Zx living team.

properties.nom_etablissement: ELLE INTERIOR STORIES, Jewelry Box, 103-105, Avenue de la Faïencerie, L-1511 Luxembourg
properties.adresse: 103-105, Avenue de la Faïencerie, L-1511 Luxembourg
properties.description_projet: Located on the top floor of an old building, this small miller's apartment, with many Interior partitions, was equipped with all essential functions. Our client fell In love with this property because of Its location, with an exceptional view of the whole city of Luxembourg. We decided to transform It Into a hotel style suite with comfortable materials, mixing nordic softness and Italian warmth. The bedroom area can be visible or hidden by a tinted glass partition.

properties.nom_etablissement: ELLE INTERIOR STORIES, Cocottes Belval, 6 Av. des Hauts-Fourneaux, 4362 Esch-sur-Alzette, Luxembourg
properties.description_projet: The challenge for EL'LE Interior stories architects was to allow the various restaurants to meet strict Integration criteria according to the city districts In which they were located. The challenge here was to fully integrate the restaurant into the historic site in which it was to take place: the blast furnaces of Belval are classified as a UNESCO World Heritage Site.

properties.nom_etablissement: ELLE INTERIOR STORIES, Société Générale- Département RH, 16-18, Boulevard Royal L-2449 Luxembourg
properties.description_projet: At the heart of Europe for over 125 years, SOCIETE GNERALE Luxembourg Is a multi-expert banking group located In the Grand Duchy. Based on the code of conduct and the values of the SOCIETE GENERALE GROUP -team spirit, commitment, Innovation and responsibility- The EL'LE Interior stories architects have redesigned the premises In order to offer the bank's numerous employees colorful spaces on a human scale and with diverse functionalities.

properties.nom_etablissement: alnoor design, The Harmonist , Los Angeles, Californie, États-Unis
properties.description_projet: Creating a new flagship boutique for a brand of high perfumery located in Los Angeles. Combining “French spirit” and contemporary attitude all the while having as foundation the plan of Master feng shui who has established the areas of fire, energy, water, prosperity etc. in the different parts of the store. This 300m2 area is clothed in black marble in colonnades, fountains in semi-precious Malachite, wooden French-style floors combined with white marble, hanging gardens, revisited furniture, Louis XV fireplace and neoclassical chandeliers made by Maison Véronèse. This architectural work uses the most beautiful materials and only the best French artisans. A cool ethereal atmosphere where historical allusions make a contrast with the luxurious modernity, place the Harmonist amongst the largest luxurious international brands.

properties.nom_etablissement: ID-wad, Kunshan, Chine, Jiangsu, Suzhou, Kunshan, Qianbang, 前浜路104
properties.adresse: Chine, Jiangsu, Suzhou, Kunshan, Qianbang, 前浜路104
properties.description_projet: Mission : Façade design, Interior, design, signage & wayfinding 19 458 m2 GLA 50 Shops Inspired by the Zhouzhuang old town, the project invites the customer to a fascinating journey along the water. The design integrates various elements that take their inspiration in the city canals whereas they are material, shapes, symbols, colours… The waves, circles, ripples are becoming a decorative frame of the project but will also inspire the shape of the furniture. Customers will find surprise and wonder in the fountain on the building front square, in the aquarium installed on the main atrium, balls pools in the animation square and interactive wall on the second floor.

properties.nom_etablissement: Humbert & Poyet, Beefbar Athenes, Athens Αστήρ Πάλας, Vouliagmeni 166 71, Grèce
properties.description_projet: For Beefbar Athens, the design was inspired by the surrounding natural elements, the sea, stone and landscape of Greece. Craftsmanship and art are underlined in the space. The tabletops are made of ceramic tiling bearing a painted design. Woven baskets hang from the restaurant ceiling. Handcrafted ceramic lighting adorn the walls. Raw materials are used throughout. The floors are all in terracotta. The furniture composed of natural woods in walnut and iroko. The bar and lounge feature a central bar with a carved pattern, a wooden bar top and large fabric suspensions. The outdoor lounge is leisurely, decorated with large sofas and ceramic tables. The composition creates a relaxed yet refined dining and lounge environment, all centered on the sea view.

properties.nom_etablissement: Atelier du Pont, Corallo Blu, Sardaigne, Italie
properties.description_projet: This villa in Sardinia enjoys a unique location, the scenery is breathtaking. The whole overlooks the crystal clear sea and nestles in the vegetation. Corallo Blu is shaped, made up of curves and soft shapes. Sculpture and architecture all at once, the village does not impose itself on nature, but spans it.

properties.nom_etablissement: Atelier du Pont, Estancia Son Jose, Alaoir, 07730, Baléares, Espagne
properties.description_projet: The Menorcan house San José is full of sunshine. It is a house that plays with contrasts: colors and rhythmic organic shapes come together to create an exceptional space. The walls, in local mares stone, have been preserved and the interior completely rehabilitated. The garden is a succession of pergolas and ponds to provide shade and freshness at any time of the day.

properties.description_projet: Those cocoons has been custom-made with many tshapes and dimensions to sit in a lounge area in Hong Kong airport. This space is still confidential so we only have picture in our workshop.

properties.nom_etablissement: ID-wad, Changyang, 1750 Changyang Rd, Yangpu District, Shanghai, Chine
properties.adresse: 1750 Changyang Rd, Yangpu District, Shanghai, Chine
properties.description_projet: Mission : Food court remodeling, lobby design, signage. 6 945 m2 GLA, 41 Shops The “food court” area is a environnement community where the consumers can collect one or more types of food in a shared area. What we observed that in china the concept of food court is not yet democratized, the restaurants are separated from each other. So we answer to this novelty by something original, a balance between traditional configuration and intertional trend of community area.

properties.nom_etablissement: Atelier du Pont, Penthouse, Barcelone, Espagne
properties.description_projet: This Barcelona penthouse pays tribute to the surrounding architecture. The organicity of the ceilings, the mesh of the materials and the details of the ornaments contribute to it. The materials, earth, marble, wood and fabrics, take different forms in all the rooms of the apartment: wall coverings, floors, tailored to the needs arrangements ... All is unitary and warm.

properties.nom_etablissement: Xavier CARTRON, Bata, Bata, Guinée Equatoriale
properties.description_projet: A Forest for the discriminating traveler, the Bata Hotel in Equatorial Guinea blurs the line between nature and urbanism. Situated high upon the Atlantic Coasts, the Hotel in Bata downtown offers exceptional views on the Atlantic Ocean from the tallest Building in Bata City. Design elements were inspired by Equatorial Guinea three ecological Typologies: The Forest, The Beach and the Sand. Because of the Unique Building Shape and its impressive Gold Metallic Mesh Skin, Bata Hotel is the First Luxurious Building on the Continental Coasts to offer a new City Eblem.

properties.nom_etablissement: Semeur d'étoiles, Triptyque Hoya, Iles Maldives
properties.description_projet: A triptych of porcelain and LEDs was created for the dining room of this island lost in the Indian Ocean. The floral work recalls the outdoor vegetation.

properties.nom_etablissement: Living Architecture Bacin Olivier (LABO), " The Coral's Safe " Piraeus Museum, Port of Piraeus, 10, Akti Miaouli str, Pireas 185 38, Grèce
properties.adresse: Port of Piraeus, 10, Akti Miaouli str, Pireas 185 38, Grèce
properties.description_projet: Redesign of existing silo and its surrounding open space into a museum. Masterplan 60 000m², Museum 15 000m² The project is the reinterpretation of the site and highlight the Industrial port history and heritage, playing with its buildings and materials. The Museography of the museum is separate in two part : one is dedicated to Underwater Antiquities and the second one to the history of the Silo. From outside, the skin of the building start to tell the stories of the underwater antiquity's world as well as what it's happening inside according to the space and program

properties.nom_etablissement: Sophie Dries Architect, Alchemia Collection, Milan, Italie
properties.description_projet: The story has begun with a blown glass in murano pendant light with mica inlays, after two years of research, was launched for the Salone del mobile 2019, created exclusively for the nilufar gallery in Milan. Sophie Dries reveals new variations with a blown glass applique light with mica and two vases that connect the transparency of the glass to the radiance of mica. She gives to mica a power of attraction, playing as a mirror that reflects light. The brass part structure is hand crafted by a Milan foundry.
