The Aquarelle is both a commercial and social space, which allows an infinite network flows and exchanges, translated into a good experience.

properties.nom_etablissement: Constance Guisset Studio, Scylla, Milan, Italie
properties.description_projet: Scylla is an immersive installation, conceived for the group show De Coding, at Palazzo Reale in Milan, at the invitation of Alcantara. Scylla proposes to decode the artworks on the walls of the room. The installation extends the imagination and the sensations: the details of the paintings and tapestries come alive to invade the room and the visitor's mind. Colossal shapes, between tentacles and fins, rise and gather around a mirror sphere reflecting the whole room. Colors and textures evoke a mysterious chimera incarning the stream of toughts. By wandering in the room or lying on the appendices, the visitor physically experience an interpretation of the mythological universe of the artworks of the Palazzo Reale. Installation imagined for the group show De Coding - Alcantara in the Tapestry Rooms, at Palazzo Reale in Milan. From April 4 to May 12 2019. Curators: Domitilla Dardi and Angela Rui.

properties.nom_etablissement: ID-wad, Kirchberg , 5 Rue Alphonse Weicker, 2721 Luxembourg
properties.description_projet: Mission : interior/exterior design, food court remodeling, signage. 25 000 m2 GLA, 66 Shops The project concerns the partial renovation of a building and more particularly of its commercial part. As part of our reflections, we explored the anchoring of the project in the building. We have therefore studied the ambitions displayed by the Luxembourg territory to put them in perspective through our approach but also observed the context and the surrounding geographical specificity and in particular the liquid element which interested us particularly to inspire the displayed commercial positioning : AFFLUENCE / OASIS / ADVANTAGE / CLEAN ENERGY FOR USERS The development axis of the proposed project therefore plays on the creation of a fluid and organic space that develops below an atrium that will retain at least in its upper part a spirit inspired by the nautical world (sailing, deck equipment …)

properties.nom_etablissement: Atelier Déambulons, Paravent, Stamford Urby - c/o Gus Ruggiero 1 Greyrock Pl - Stamford CT 06901 (USA)
properties.adresse: Stamford Urby - c/o Gus Ruggiero 1 Greyrock Pl - Stamford CT 06901 (USA)
properties.description_projet: In collaboration with Noé Duchaufour Lawrance studio, we’ve build a piece of scenography for the Stamford Urby hotel in New-York. The project is a screen with a geometric braiding pattern in bamboo slats. This piece of crafts is a part of many others pieces from all around the world: carpets from J. Staron, raku tales made bu Fabienne l’Hostis, desk build by Arca and vegetation design by around plantscaping.

properties.nom_etablissement: STUDIO MHNA, Club Med Sanlang , Chengdu, Sichuan, Chine
properties.description_projet: Located in central southwest China, not far from the city of Chengdu and UNESCO World Heritage sites, a new Club Med Village will open its doors in 2022. The project, entrusted to Studio MHNA in collaboration with Montaigne Design, takes place in a preserved nature with a breathtaking panoramic view of the mountains. The decoration is inspired by this surrounding nature, sublimated in various artistic, playful or poetic and always contemporary forms. The hotel has 356 guest rooms, 2 restaurants, a spa, and all the necessary facilities that make this place absolutely unique.

properties.nom_etablissement: Xavier CARTRON, Mandarin Oriental Muscat, Mascate, Oman
properties.description_projet: The project is situated in the center of Muscat, 20 minutes away from Muscat International Airport, in the area of Shatti Al Qurum. The plot spreads on 32,570m²;its north boundary is on the beachfront, while its west boundary is adjacent to a natural Wadi. The New Shatti al Qurum Hotel - Muscat, Oman to be operated by Mandarin Oriental, aims to deliver a 5-star seaside hotel experience for hospitality and mixed-use development composed of the following : Luxury Five Star Hotel: 200 Keys - GFA circa 29,000 m², Serviced Apartments: 200 Units - GFA circa 26,000 m², Retail Component: GFA circa 4,000 m², Xavier Cartron was commissioned to Design and Supervise the Construction of more than 44,000 m² of Hotel and Apartments Areas within the Project Complex. The design intent was to feel at home with a Omani Touch to relate to the place.

properties.nom_etablissement: STUDIO MHNA, Hotel Movenpick Abidjan, Le Plateau, Abidjan, Côte d'Ivoire
properties.description_projet: A 5-star luxury hotel, whose interior design and decoration has been entrusted to Studio MHNA, the Mövenpick Abidjan will be inaugurated in early 2021. It is located in the Plateau business district, in Abidjan, Ivory Coast, and has 160 rooms including 5 suites and 6 junior suites. It is a place dedicated to art, "the art of contrasts between tradition and modernity", in the image of the city that hosts it.

properties.nom_etablissement: emmanuelle moureaux architecture + design, 1000 COLORS WAVE, Imabari City Auditorium, Japon, 〒794-0026 Ehime, Imabari, Bekkucho, 1 Chome−４−1
properties.adresse: Imabari City Auditorium, Japon, 〒794-0026 Ehime, Imabari, Bekkucho, 1 Chome−４−1
properties.description_projet: Imabari City in Ehime Prefecture is known for its quality towels and for its leading textile dyeing industry. For the “IMABARI Color Show” introducing the dyeing technology in Imabari City, Emmanuelle revealed an installation "1000 COLORS WAVE", using her own 1000 (one thousand) colors palette specially created for the exhibition. It is the second installation realized for the “IMABARI Color Show” after the 2017-2018 exhibitions in Spiral Garden and Imabari City. Even though the same water, formula, and environment are utilized during the dyeing process, the slightest change in weather and/or temperature can completely disrupt the result of the pigmentation. However, in the skilled hands of the craftsmen of Imabari, the dye process is so precise, 1000 unique colors of fabrics are possible. One thousand pieces of textile specially dyed in 1000 different colors covered the 1002 seats of the Imabari City Auditorium, designed by the famous architect Kenzo Tange. The bright colors palette gave off an energy that created an astounding wave of colors which engaged with the ceiling of the public hall.

properties.nom_etablissement: Philippe Hurel, Rocca Residence, Colorado, États-Unis
properties.description_projet: Philippe Hurel participated in the development of this exceptional private residence through one of his loyal clients: Studio Allen Kisch based in Dallas. The interior reflects the surrounding landscape, vast and warm. Wood and the mineral universe dominate this haven of peace posed like an observatory of nature.

properties.nom_etablissement: Maxime d'Angeac architecture, Villa H, Portugal
properties.description_projet: Villa for a contemporary art collector with sophisticated techniques in order to create the « grand style » that client wanted.. The projet consisted to create an ideal « set » for art collection where all periods are mixed between Neo-classical bespoke furniture and strongly contemporary art. The whole project - interior design and furniture - were designed by Maxime D’Angeac studio and produced with best French artisan makers. Noble materials such as marble, ebony, lacquer, polished stainless steel, alabaster were employed.

properties.nom_etablissement: Atelier du Pont, Mi Casa, Casa de campo, Minorque, Baléares, Espagne
properties.description_projet: Menorca, the least touristy of the Balearic Islands, is known for its well-preserved cultural heritage and natural environment. The rural landscape is dotted with inlets of crystal-clear, turquoise-blue water. A casa de campo, in the middle of the fields, all in white – it has “vacation” written all over it. The fuchsia bougainvillea explodes against the immaculate facades, and the sea in the distance completes the landscape. The whiteness of the walls, floors, and roofs, accented with the occasional dash of bright, vigorous color, create an ambiance that is comfortable and refreshing. The rural landscape of dry stone walls, fields of wild olive trees, black horses, sheep, donkeys, tortoises and birds are sure to surprise and enchant.

properties.nom_etablissement: AW², Wink Hotel Saigon Centre, 75 Nguyễn Bỉnh Khiêm, Đa Kao, Quận 1, Thành phố Hồ Chí Minh, Vietnam
properties.adresse: 75 Nguyễn Bỉnh Khiêm, Đa Kao, Quận 1, Thành phố Hồ Chí Minh, Vietnam
properties.description_projet: Creation of the Wink affordable lifestyle hotel brand: 237 bedrooms, coworking spaces, café, gym The Wink concept sees AW² move towards a new architectural typology in the hospitality realm – the medium-rise urban hotel. The Wink brand is directly born out of the evolution that the hotel industry is currently undergoing. Wink brings us into this new era with its pop culture energy and blended spaces where accommodation, work and leisure cohabit. This twenty-first century hospitality product is targeted at a new generation of traveller, one that is constantly connected and seeking a hotel experience that rhymes with their epoque. The Wink brand has been designed by AW² to attract this new hotel clientele. The Wink hotels are fashionable urban destinations where the next generation of influencers will go to stay, have a drink, enjoy Vietnamese cuisine or simply use their laptops in the coworking spaces. The project brings Vietnamese street life into the lobby and public areas of the hotel with street life-inspired furniture designed by AW² and an interior design that resonates with the outside urban environment. A specific colour palette has been created for the brand by AW² and can be found throughout the hotel – from the scale of the bespoke cushion fabrics to the sunshades on the facades. The 237 hotel rooms have been laid out over eleven floors. They are conceived to be efficient in space requirements, modern, creative pods that provide the guests with all comforts in a stylish, minimalist setting. Overall, the project focuses on creating a balance between design forwardness, financial return and construction feasibility. In this way, the Wink brand is a contrast of traditional style with modern forward-thinking originality. It aims to deliver vibrant, innovative experiences for all its guests and users. The Wink brand is the transmission of AW²’s savoir-faire in resort architecture to an urban context and will roll out across Vietnam over several sites in the years to come.

properties.nom_etablissement: Nathalie Rives A Design, Hotel Ambassador, Spissstrasse 10, 3920 Zermatt, Suisse
properties.description_projet: Renovation of the lobby and restaurant on the ground floor and a lounge and spa club at R-1. A project of about 600 square feet in Zermatt in Switzerland with natural materials: wood, lime but also fabrics of large publishing houses.

properties.nom_etablissement: Studio Catoir, Kuchenatelier, Kuchenatelier, Gewandhaus Dresden, Ringstraße 1, 01067 Dresden, Deutschland
properties.adresse: Kuchenatelier, Gewandhaus Dresden, Ringstraße 1, 01067 Dresden, Deutschland
properties.description_projet: Interior design for a delux patisserie Kuchenatelier, located in the lobby of the Gewandhaus Dresden, a five-star boutique hotel part of the Autograph Collection. With a passion for fresh products the show-patisserie of the Kuchenatelier creates moments of joy and happiness. Showcasing five-star cakes in an elegant and discerning interior. Studio Catoir provided a complete design package, from corporate identity,to tableware, and from interior design to staff uniform.

properties.nom_etablissement: STUDIO MHNA, Café Abidjan & Galerie Nour , Le Plateau, Abidjan, Côte d'Ivoire
properties.description_projet: In the heart of the Plateau business district in Abidjan, Ivory Coast, Studio MHNA designed a typical Parisian brasserie at the request of the owners. A gastronomic bistro whose decoration restores all these classical registers in a lighter and more contemporary way. It features revisited decorative and characteristic elements: woodwork and mirrors, iconic tiles, brass hangings and chandeliers, marble, seats... This venue will be inaugurated in 2021.

properties.nom_etablissement: LUX, Digital Display, Albert Mangelsdorff Weiher, Bockenheimer Anlage, 60313 Frankfurt am Main
properties.adresse: Albert Mangelsdorff Weiher, Bockenheimer Anlage, 60313 Frankfurt am Main
properties.description_projet: For the Luminale 2020 we designed a light object with the objective of “re-poetization of the digital” through one massive pager sending romantic messages to all people in Frankfurt. An alphanumeric Sixteen-segment display as a digital screen communicate with light as a medium. Firstly, Romantic sentences created by the masters of this movement use the digital interface to send their messages;and secondly, the digital display will try with his own language made of codes, emoticons and glitch to communicate in its own way. In this installation, light becomes a new medium of communication.

properties.nom_etablissement: Charles Zana, Boutique Cartier, 360 MALL, Jassem Mohamed Al Kharafi Rd Block 7, Al Zahraa South Surra، 13151, Koweït
properties.adresse: 360 MALL, Jassem Mohamed Al Kharafi Rd Block 7, Al Zahraa South Surra، 13151, Koweït
properties.description_projet: The design of Cartier’s new boutique in C.C Kuwait 360 evokes the trends Cartier has observed in its client experiences and meets the expectations of the “new generation” of young Kuwaitis in a privileged location. The essence of the project is anchored in the country and plays on a mix of references such as its traditions (moucharabiehs, brasswork, weaving), landscape (sand dunes, sun, sea) and extreme modernity (daring, innovative, futurist architecture).

properties.nom_etablissement: Semeur d'étoiles, Hoya, Luxembourg
properties.description_projet: Unique composition of several Nature and Harmony panels composed of hand-modeled porcelain (Hoya) lit by LEDs. In a double-height duplex, the installation plays with the frame and the slope of the roof.

properties.nom_etablissement: emmanuelle moureaux architecture + design, mirai, GREEN SPRINGS, Japon, 〒190-0014 Tokyo, Tachikawa, Midoricho, ３丁目１
properties.adresse: GREEN SPRINGS, Japon, 〒190-0014 Tokyo, Tachikawa, Midoricho, ３丁目１
properties.description_projet: Emmanuelle Moureaux’s first public art sculpture has been unveiled in the new well-being distric in Tokyo, Japan. The sculpture is titled ‘mirai’, meaning ‘the future’ in Japanese. As part of Moureaux’s ongoing ‘100 colors’ installation series, ‘mirai’ visualizes the next 100 years to come (2020 to 2119) in 100 different shades of colors. Standing at 4 meters in height, composed of 400 layered big numbers, the structure of the sculpture provides a big enough gap in between the years to allow children to interact with the piece. Furthermore, when looking inside the body of the sculpture, passersby will notice that the colorful future is in fact supported structurally by the past, which is represented by white numbers. ‘mirai’ is on permanent display in GREEN SPRINGS at the tachikawa stage garden entrance plaza.

properties.nom_etablissement: Constance Guisset Studio, Chiaroscuro, Milan, Italie
properties.description_projet: The Institut Français in Milan invites designer Constance Guisset to celebrate a decade of creation during a solo show in april 2021. During this carte blanche, the visitor would be invited to discover the artist’s work through the theme of the oxymoron, as a quest for balance. Balance between gravity and lightness, full and empty, clear and dark, tension and flexibility, movement and immobility... It would embodies the constant search of the designer to advance on a crest line, to create objects by the work of shapes, lines and materials. This exploration would be illustrated in the presentation of a selection of Constance Guisset’s work, between design and scenographies, exclusive and older creations. It would be a spectacular journey: the creations would become the characters of a play in progress and offer themselves to the eye in surreal acts. This feeling would be reinforced by the work of light and sound, as the visitor becomes the spectator of a looped play during the time of the tour of the exhibition. The light could be worked in different ways: pursuit highlighting the objects successively, colored projections transforming the objects and their environment... This spectacular dimension would also be shown in the projection space, where we could discover the scenographies of ballets made by Constance Guisset. On the ground, we would find a reminder of the scenography made for Angelin Preljocaj’s Winterreise at La Scala in Milan. The finishing of the exhibited objects would also embody this theme: they would be given a new look and would be presented only in a variation of black and white and in a wide variety of materials. This work of textures would invite to discover the creations as they have never been seen before. Visitors would be invited to touch the objects or even try them, when possible (armchairs, chairs, tables ...), to extend this sensitive adventure. This exhibition would take place in the special location that is the Institut Français in Milan. Like this emblematic place for exchanges between two cultures, the exhibition would be an opportunity to present projects carried out with numerous European, and more particularly Italian, design editors. These essential collaborations would have a good place in the project, with the presentation of objects imagined for Zanotta, Molteni & C, La Cividina or Bosa. Still in this perspective of exchanges and transmission, the exhibition could be an opportunity to organize meetings with students, for example. The exhibition is curated by Domitilla Dardi, in charge of the MAXXI Design collection in Rome. The graphic designer is Agnès Dahan Studio. The light designer is Studio Vaste.

properties.nom_etablissement: Constance Guisset Studio, Wintereisse, Milan, Italie
properties.description_projet: Fourth collaboration with choreographer Angelin Preljocaj, Winterreise is a mythical romantic piece of music. It evokes the arrival of the man at the twilight of his life. This feeling is embodied on stage by an almost naked scene, covered in black snow and slowly turning into a winter garden. The moments of intense melancholy are crossed by instants of joy, lights being colored little by little and glittering on the snow or radiant shines of colors. These happy memories punctuate the journey while remaining inaccessible, like a distant landscape seen from the window of a train. Show premiere at La Scala in Milan, January 2019. From October 3 to 5 at Théâtre des Champs Elysées, Paris. Choreography : Angelin Preljocaj Music : Franz Schubert Scenography : Constance Guisset Lights : Eric Soyer Bass baritone : Thomas Tatzl Piano-forte : James Vaughan With the dancers of the Ballet Preljocaj
properties.credits_photo: Winterrese ph Brescia e Amisano Teatro alla Scala - Andrea Risso e Christian Fagetti

properties.nom_etablissement: Mésarchitecture - Didier Faustino, XYZ Lounge, Zebrastraat 32, 9000 Gent, Belgique
properties.description_projet: The architectural intervention on the XYZ Lounge, a 360m² surface area, aims at redefining the use and the volumes of the public spaces: entrance hall, central nave and bar, lateral rooms and mezzanine platforms leading to the conference halls and meeting rooms. A made to measure metallic frame imposes a new outline for the space, supporting the walls and ceilings that have been brought in. The lounge spans out into three spaces from the entrance: an open space on the left hand side, for cocktails and evening parties, an adjoining bar below the central nave and a smaller open space on the right hand side with an access to the terrace. The furniture, designed specifically for the space, is composed of fixed elements made of marble, of high tables and chairs and of a series of rotomoulded seats in polypropylene.

properties.nom_etablissement: Studio Jean-Philippe Nuel, Sofitel Rome Villa Borghese, Via Lombardia, 47, 00187 Roma RM, Italie
properties.description_projet: The positioning of the Sofitel Villa Borghese in Rome is seen as a link between French culture and Italy, the country where the hotel has taken root. The project combines Art de vivre and culture from both countries which are close and often have common pasts. It is conceived as a dialogue between French elegance tinged with Classicism and Refinement and the Italian Baroque tinged with Opulence and Generosity.

properties.nom_etablissement: Laurent Maugoust Architecture, Chairman suite, Hyatt Regency Tokyo Bay, 5-chōme-8-23 Akemi, Urayasu-shi, Chiba, Japan, 279-0014
properties.titre_affiche: Chairman suite, Hyatt Regency Tokyo Bay
properties.description_projet: The Chairman Suite is 1,732 square feet, and Laurent Maugoust expressed the Haussmann style French apartment influenced by Paris’s legendary fashion houses and luxurious palaces. The designer’s vision was to create a dynamic combination of traditional French opulence, modern design elements, and a high-quality decorative style that reflects the hotel owner’s objective of defining luxury for the Chairman Suite.

properties.nom_etablissement: emmanuelle moureaux architecture + design, Slices of Time, NOW Gallery, The Gateway Pavilions, Peninsula Square, Soames Walk, London SE10 0SQ, Royaume-Uni
properties.adresse: NOW Gallery, The Gateway Pavilions, Peninsula Square, Soames Walk, London SE10 0SQ, Royaume-Uni
properties.description_projet: Inspired by the location of the gallery, near to the Greenwich Meridian marking time, "Slices of Time" expresses the past, the now and the future through 168,000 small numbers composing 120 "slices" of time, hanged in the space, as a round representation of the earth floating. Composed of 100 layers of numbers in 100 shades of colors and 20 layers of numbers in white, the installation visualizes the next 100 years to come (2020 to 2119) and the past 20 years (2000 to 2019) represented in white. “Slices of Time” is part of Emmanuelle’s "100 colors" installation series.

properties.nom_etablissement: Stephane Parmentier, Casa Minotto, Pointe Milou, 97133, Saint-Barthélemy
properties.description_projet: Residential villas project in Saint-Barth -Pointe Milou.

properties.nom_etablissement: Nazak Design, 1904 Beaux ArtsBuilding Manhattan UWS, 344 W 72nd St, New York, NY 10023, États-Unis
properties.adresse: 344 W 72nd St, New York, NY 10023, États-Unis
properties.description_projet: My husband Bill and I were ready for a change. I was looking for something large and rambling, perhaps on the East Side as a change of direction, and ideally in “estate condition” requiring a total rebuild. That would be more work but a labor of love as it would provide the opportunity for re-expression of every detail, from the layout to the last ornamental touch. But, another accident—in the apartment hunt, I came across a 1900 Beaux Art building on the opposite side of Manhattan, the Upper West Side. It was as close as it comes to a Paris building on a New York avenue, and I fell in love. The available space combined three apartments into a single unit with four bedrooms, three baths, a powder room, and an open kitchen. The bones weren’t just good—they were spectacular. But the floorplan needed to be rearranged and the interior aesthetics updated. So rather than a gut renovation, we focused on the adjustments and finishing touches necessary to restore the space to its former glory: new doors, new floors, new lighting, new fixtures, new millwork. Transforming the dark fourth bedroom into an inviting library was one of the major challenges. We achieved that by breaking open the wall and replacing it with a wafer-thin, high-gloss navy-blue door that could slide shut (to ensure quiet and privacy when necessary) or open widely (to allow the light from the street to tumble in). The custom-built door was far too large for the 1904-sized elevator bank, and so had to be delivered in pieces and assembled in the apartment. Another challenge was the kitchen. In the plan we inherited, the cooking space opened to the dining room, with a shared marble counter between the rooms. Open kitchens can be wonderful, of course, but I felt the restrained elegance of the building called for slightly more formality. But the marble countertop that extending out from the kitchen presented a puzzle—cutting it was risky, but leaving it jutting out into the dining room was out of the question. We solved the puzzle by sealing up the original opening, installing modern floor-to-ceiling cabinetry on the dining room with two sections divided by the white marble line of the counter, finished in anthracite steel. And to brighten the kitchen we added a brushed brass backsplash as well as a row of functional upper cabinets. As is so often the case, the final finishes weave the elements together. Herringbone wood floors were refinished to show natural oak;closet doors in the large dressing areas were dressed in gray panels, handles and fixtures throughout the space feature specialty brass from a favorite London vendor. We finished with a mix of contemporary French and Italian furnishings and decorative objects, designed to marry contemporary European style with a uniquely and traditionally Manhattan space.

properties.nom_etablissement: Xavier CARTRON, Résidence Koweit, Koweit City, Koweit
properties.description_projet: The project is located in Salwa district, Kuwait, overlooking the main road (Belajat road) from the one side, and a residential back street. The entire site is neighbored by one existing residential building from one side and a walk alley separating from neighbor on the other side. The main plot totaling 7,000 m² comprises of the following components: The Main Residence, Landscape, Future Development - 4 Villas. The Main Residence Project 1,500 m² Plot and the Landscape 3,000 m² has a total built-up area exceeding 4,000 m². Special request for a “French Classic" style Residence by the sea. The Ground Floor consists of guest reception areas and family area open to a back garden, the First Floor includes the Children areas and the Top Floor includes Monsieur et Madame Master areas which are open to a large loggia overlooking the sea. A grand Staircase in French Style lit by a skylight links the different levels of the residence.

properties.nom_etablissement: Charles Zana, Appartement 39 Quai Wilson, 39 Quai Wilson Genève, Suisse
properties.description_projet: Located in an iconic building on Quai Wilson, this apartment has a French Riviera feel, the apartment's large windows offer a panoramic view of the landscape over Lake Leman and Mont Blanc. While respecting the architecture of this apartment, Charles Zana has rethought the distribution of the rooms to create a more fluid and contemporary circulation. Surface : 250 m2, Colaboration : Les Ateliers Jouffre New-York

properties.nom_etablissement: Moinard Bétaille, Yunjac Spa JW Marriott, Seoul, Corée du Sud
properties.description_projet: Nature has conquered the spaces of the Yunjac Spa, which invite contemplation as well as relaxation. With their minds elsewhere and their attention wandering, the visitor can enjoy the interplay of materials. Enveloped in volumes of just the right proportions, reassured by the plaster bas-reliefs of plant inspiration, it breaks with the hectic city life.

properties.nom_etablissement: Sybille de Margerie, Cocon de Luxe, Italy
properties.description_projet: A follower of spiritual retreats, lockdown provided great food for thought for the interior designer. This new creation is a manifesto for “living better”, where well-being is more than ever a luxury in the heart of the creative process. It is a new design concept, in the form of a gîte, whose purpose is to inspire hoteliers and developers as an extension of an existing establishment or a second home in the great outdoors. Le Cocon de Luxe is a refuge, an escape free of constraints, which is rich in fulfilment and softness. Ovoid shaped, the space is intimate and feminine, designed to be like a symbol of eternity where once can imagine reaching out the mystery of creation and life. In this sensorial and dreamlike universe, one seeks the perfect symbiosis with the cosmos, a retreat without a beginning, nor an end. It is a space to isolate, alone or as a couple, and awaken one’s senses to a benevolent nature, rich in positivity and inspiration. One can curl up to revitalise oneself, to escape from the everyday city-living pressures, to protect oneself from a world which has become so worrisome. Wide openings play between the indoor and outdoor boundaries to create a sense of freedom and space. Inside, a day area and a night area, are connected together. The fluid layout follows a path of elliptical curves which wrap around the space without restricting the flow. Sybille de Margerie was inspired by Marcel Proust’s ponderings : ‘‘the most remarkable journeys come from the inside, free from time and space’’. In this soft nest, the senses are awakened: creativity, the imagination and dreams are emphasised. It is a place for meditation, reading, and resting within a cosy cocoon. The space is simultaneously luxurious and comforting, wrapped with noble and raw textures, echoing the surrounding nature. The interior includes wood and raw stone flooring, glass inlayed with iron fabric, brass, warm wooden fittings, leather, cotton, linen and velvet cushions. Colourful wallpaper and carpets bring a dynamic and poetic touch. The furniture is nomadic, easy to make bespoke and to move around. Rooted in its era, it is contemporary and full of dynamism. You will find a “vintage” spirit, referring to the big names in design, as many landmarks and safe values. Luxury is hidden;it is felt more than it is shown. It is expressed in a myriad of details, from the sophistication of a doorknob to the tieback for curtains.

properties.nom_etablissement: Charles Zana, Yatch My Asteria, Nouvelle-Zélande
properties.description_projet: For this 50's yacht, Charles Zana has chosen comfortable furniture with refined lines that invite relaxation and travel. The elegant lighting emphasizes the clean lines of the yacht's elegant decoration.

properties.nom_etablissement: Saguez & Partners, Überseequartier, Hambourg, Allemagne
properties.description_projet: "SEESIDE DISTRICT" New life in the city of future. Development of a new lifestyle district in the old Elbe docks, taking inspiration from a new openness to maritime trade and the outside world. Tourism, leisure and housing, creating a new urban and rural connection between the river and historic city centre of Hamburg. With the architects HPP, UN Studios, Christian de Porzamparc, and the landscapist Beth Galli.

properties.nom_etablissement: Aurelien Chen, Renovation of the coal mine workers' canteen, Jinxing, Shijiazhuang, China
properties.titre_affiche: Renovation of the coal mine workers' canteen
properties.description_projet: The refurbishment of this industrial heritage, designed by French architect Aurelien Chen, is a subtle interpretation of China’s “red” era. This building used to be the canteen of the coal mine’s workers. It is located next to the former office buildings, which were built in 1912 and are typical of western architecture from that time, with intensive use of arch elements. The work consists in refurbishing the existing dilapidated building and slightly transforming the facades in order to create a homogeneity with adjacent historical buildings. The interior design is the result of a careful historical study of “red” era’s colors, materials and furniture, which were subtly interpreted. Finally, this refurbishment was meant to adapt the building to new and contemporary usage. At the center of the main hall, there is a vibrant element that recreates,, in an abstract way, a pattern of “flower with a star at the center”. This pattern, typical of China’s red era, was originally located on the dilapidated ceiling that had to be demolished. This central element has multiple functions : information desk, exhibition space, rest area, “round table” discussion, etc. The existing old dilapidated walls, with their historical traces, are the witnesses of the red era. The design focuses on these walls, they become the key elements of the spaces. Arch elements were missing to create the link with adjacent historical buildings. During the construction process, some arches were discovered in the walls, as well a basement made of stone vaults, and all of them have been emphasized by the design. Stairs leading to the basement were moved inside a new volume made of arches that was added on the façade. Two voids create a strong visual link between the main hall and the basement. Design Institute partner : Urban and rural planning and design institute of CSCEC

properties.nom_etablissement: Thierry Lemaire, Chalet Saanen , Gstaad, Saanen, Suisse
properties.description_projet: A beautiful unit hangs over this chalet dating from the 16th century thanks to the cohabitation of authentic wood-based materials left in its own juice. Thierry Lemaire's furniture with strong character mixed with vintage pieces brings a warm and comfortable soul to this setting. Reconciling a traditional spirit and a contemporary vein, Thierry Lemaire has worked on a certain rusticity in order to bring this old chalet into modernity without however drawing a line on its soul.

properties.nom_etablissement: dach&zephir, Plant Fever , Le Grand Hornu, Rue Sainte-Louise 82, 7301 Boussu, Belgique
properties.adresse: Le Grand Hornu, Rue Sainte-Louise 82, 7301 Boussu, Belgique
properties.description_projet: Exposition de la collection Éritaj Kontré (collaboration avec la Faïencerie Georges et le vannier Gérard Ako)

properties.nom_etablissement: Isabelle Stanislas, Chelsea, Londres, UK, Earls Court Square, Londres SW5 9UL, Royaume-Uni
properties.adresse: Earls Court Square, Londres SW5 9UL, Royaume-Uni
properties.description_projet: With windows overlooking a London garden and courtyard, I invited the natural light to elegantly lift and percolate this apartment. Here, Parisian chic meets London archi- tecture. The sun’s rays hang in the air and gracefully move along the white walls with their original moldings and fireplaces. This sense of weightlessness is created in contrast with the dark grounding of the floors. The city’s hyperactivity gently comes to rest here amid the comfort of cotton, velvet, and linen, where the owner couple’s different cultural backgrounds mingle in a harmony of straight lines.

properties.nom_etablissement: Constance Guisset Studio, Exhibition Edit Napoli, Naples, Italie
properties.description_projet: Exhibition of objects at the Edit Napoli fair in Naples in June 2019.

properties.nom_etablissement: RICH DESIGNERS, CluMed Cefalu *****,Club Med Sicile, Cefalu, Sicile, Italie
properties.description_projet: Following a diagnostic on a previous lighting project, Rich came up with new perspective and carried out a new lighting project for Club Med Exclusive Collection 5Ψ Resort in Cefalù, Sicily, Italy, for all interiors and terraces of the Resort. The program is large: guest bungalows, SPA, main restaurants and terraces, reception, fitness area and bars for newbuilt spaces and, restaurants and bars located in the historic "Palazzo" building. Incorporating the interior architect's design, we sought to create a golden atmosphere and soft integration into the architecture. We selected a range of discrete and efficient lighting fixtures targeting an elegant luminous ambience.
properties.credits_photo: King & Roselli & Sophie Jacqmin interior design

properties.nom_etablissement: STUDIO MHNA, Saint Régis Bora Bora Resort , Bora Bora 98730, Polynésie Française
properties.description_projet: A pearl in the middle of the ocean, the St Regis Bora Bora Resort, a 5-star luxury hotel, regains its lustre with the intervention of Studio MHNA. In search of the perfect balance between a luxurious atmosphere - the very idea of this paradisiacal destination - and a tribute to the surrounding nature. Natural materials such as mother-of-pearl, shells, driftwood, mixed with worked woods, deep contemporary lacquers and golden bronzes reinforce this desire for totally exclusive comfortable and dreamlike exoticism.

properties.nom_etablissement: Léonard Kadid, Pavillon Panoramah, Messe Basel, Suisse
properties.description_projet: Pavilion made of aluminium foam for the window company Panoramah. Like monoliths organised in a primitive layout, the elements composing the pavilion have all the same section. Two beams supported by four columns are holding 5m tall windows with different lengths. Together with sliding or pivoting opening systems, these windows are defining different spaces within the pavilion. One of the column is recessed from the edge to allow a third beam to be placed on the platform. Standing on IPN profiles, this beam is a 4m long desk defining a meeting area. Four Athens stool made of stained black solid oak allow the visitors to rest while experiencing new perspectives. The pavilion was exhibited in Basel, Switzerland during SwissBau 2020.

properties.nom_etablissement: Studio Adrien Gardère, Drishyakala Art Museum, New Delhi, Inde
properties.description_projet: Studio Adrien Gardère designed the Drishyakala Art Museum for DAG New Delhi - Mumbai - New York and in collaboration with the Archeological Survey of India (ASI). The unique 2500m2 museum is located in the heart of the UNESCO world heritage site: Delhi Red Fort Barrack n° 4. For its opening, the Drishyakala Art Museum explores the development of modern Indian art from the 18th century onwards, exhibiting more than 400 works by India's greatest artists.

properties.nom_etablissement: ELLE INTERIOR STORIES, Abbaye de Neumünster, 28, rue Münster L-2160 Luxembourg
properties.description_projet: The Centre Culturel de Rencontre Abbaye de Neumünster has chosen, in 2019, to reinvent itself. EL'LE has the privilege to propose specific insertions benefiting from a spectacular setting. This architectural complex, which has known 4 centuries of eventful history, is today devoted to cultural projects, and is at the same time a wonderful setting for large events. On its 12,000 m2, nearly 700 events are organized each year in this place open to all, which is a meeting place open to the dialogue of cultures and to the culture of dialogue. Over the next five years, EL'LE will inscribe its contemporary lines in the three buildings that make up this cultural Mecca. The reception-boutique will be the first strong intervention: this box-sculpture will take pride of place in an open space. Deliberately treated with strong lines, the mirrored exterior cladding will reflect the historical structure of the building. The interior walls of the imposing box, treated in bright yellow, will mark its new identity. The documents representing the project include a plan, a diagram developing the insertion of the box in the existing volume, and a perspective. The project will be completed in early 2022.

properties.nom_etablissement: Charles Zana, Appartement 520 Park Avenue, 520 Park Avenue, New York, Etats-Unis
properties.description_projet: Suspended in the sky of New-York, this apartment has an amazing view of Uptown and Central Park with its large bay windows. The skillful arrangement of the space and the choice of neutral colors show off an exceptional collection of contemporary art to its best advantage. Surface : 430m2, Colaborations : Les Ateliers Jouffre, Galerie Friedman Benda

properties.nom_etablissement: Moinard Bétaille, Hôtel Cala di Volpe, Hotel Cala di Volpe, a Luxury Collection Hotel, Costa Smeralda, SP160, 07021 Capriccioli SS, Italie
properties.adresse: Hotel Cala di Volpe, a Luxury Collection Hotel, Costa Smeralda, SP160, 07021 Capriccioli SS, Italie
properties.description_projet: Chosen to continue the history of the Cala di Volpe hotel, Bruno Moinard and Claire Bétaille have been respectful to the spirit of the place, overlooking the crystal-clear waters of the Smeralda coast in Sardinia since 1963. They have revisited the codes of this architectural-sculptural jewel, reviving the uniqueness of this curved Mediterranean Eden. Faithful to the gestures of the architect Jacques Couëlle and his son Savin, they pay homage to this complete work of art and, with small touches of comfort and modernity, place it in its century.

properties.nom_etablissement: Aurelien Chen, Chinese liquor boutique hotel, Yan'an, Shaanxi, Chine
properties.description_projet: A sensorial journey through the making of traditional Chinese wine. In China, alcohol is made from cereals seeds, following the same process for centuries. After a careful study of this process, we created a specific architectural scenography that gives the visitor the opportunity to experience the process of making Chinese wine. At the entrance, various seeds are placed in Plexiglas tubes to create a vibrant screen with a huge pattern. In the rooms, seeds were directly integrated inside the paint of the walls, resulting in a very specific texture. More generally, warm tones and shades of brown and ochre remind of the topic of the seeds. Alcohol is traditionally placed in ceramic jars for fermentation. They are usually made of very dark ceramic with shades of purple or dark red. When entering the entrance lobby, visitor stands on a transparent carpet made of glass. Underneath lie a series of jars that are half buried, giving the illusion of ancient jars. This carpet extends to the outdoor space and becomes a water fountain. The sequences of circulation become obvious. Calm and elegant atmospheres, use of black marble for the front desk and of black wood for furniture, remind of black ceramic jars. Vegetal materials are often used to fasten the fermentation process. They are compacted and stored as bricks. We used these vegetal bricks to create the counter of the bar, which gives an olfactive experience to the user. The countertop is made of custom terrazzo, with pieces of alcohol glass bottles integrated in it. Pieces of furniture, lamps, as well as the plaited fabrics used for wall and ceiling covering, remind of the traditional tools that are used for the making of alcohol: wicker baskets and sieves, etc. Outdoor spaces are part of this sensorial course, creating a continuity between interior and exterior. The installation located in the main courtyard reminds the transformation of liquid, from steam to condensation in drop of alcohol. Collaborator : Zhijian Workshop : Aurelien Chen (lead) + Wang Ke Yao

properties.nom_etablissement: Bismut&Bismut, Yacht SD118, Viareggio, 55049 Lucques, Italia
properties.description_projet: Interior design of the new yacht SD118 from SanLorenzo shipyards.

properties.nom_etablissement: Elliott Barnes Interiors, Cloud Nine / The Rhine 740 Tower - Penthouse Project Dusseldorf, Düsseldorf, Allemagne
properties.titre_affiche: Cloud Nine / The Rhine 740 Tower - Penthouse Project Dusseldorf
properties.description_projet: We have all lived that moment where our performance at last allows us to rise and float above the fray and commotion. When we achieve that moment, it is often said that life becomes so light that we have the sensation of walking on a cloud. The CLOUD NINE project is a testament to that moment, to that achievement. Through a dialogue of counterpoints between architectural details, design details and exceptional historical and contemporary furniture, Elliott Barnes proposes an interior experience entitled CLOUD NINE. The “mise en scene” of themes such as: cloudscape ( (hear the music of Philip Glass), walking on thin air, a room with a view, and clouds with silver lining support the general narrative, inspired from the 1968 hit song, of the same name, by the legendary group from Motown, The Temptations. The goal of the Elliott Barnes Interiors Interior Design Concept is to create a unique elegant and spectacular interior environment. The unexpected meetings of past and future, forms, materials and furniture, will result in a singular, familiar yet novel, atmosphere. Particular attention will be given to highlighting the views of the surrounding landscape punctuated by the Rhine River. By modulating the floor plane to create an interior landscape, the visitor will experience a feeling of “légèrté”, joy and happiness.

properties.nom_etablissement: Nazak Design, Prewar Manhattan Upper West Side, 685 West End Avenue, New York, NY, 10025
properties.adresse: 685 West End Avenue, New York, NY, 10025
properties.description_projet: One of the great and fun challenges of interior design in New York is to turn small spaces into big ones—projects we sometimes call “Mission Impossible.” Because of high real estate prices and scarce inventory for desirable pre-war buildings, Manhattanites are forever trying to cram more into less. So when one lovely client called to ask how could she turn her “Classic Six”—a 1927 two bedroom apartment—into a four bedroom layout sufficient to meet the needs of her growing family, it was just another day on the job. The building had great bones: high ceilings and large airy rooms. The challenge was to somehow create two additional rooms with the same floor space, without sacrificing the elegant flow. We settled on a plan to borrow space from the formal dining room (which was outsized by contemporary standards), shave a bit of territory from one of the pre-existing bedrooms, reconfigure large but inefficient walk in closet and enlarging the maid’s room, into modern storage, slightly redirect the main corridor in the apartment, and from those adjustments conjure a third and fourth bedroom—each small but comfortable, serviced by a shared bathroom and modern closets. Even better, we were able to maintain the couple’s master bedroom in its original generous size, update the en suite bath with Carrera marble and double sinks, and—using just a bit more of the recovered dining room space—create a spacious walk-in closet for the master suite. The bright and large living room was updated but retained its grand and welcoming proportions. To replace the old dining room, we designed a gallery at the mouth of the corridor that functioned as overflow entertaining space as well as a dining area. The renovated kitchen featured upgraded appliances, Italian tile work and a stainless steel backsplash. Along the way, we updated the floor, the AC and AV system and installed modern hidden storage throughout. Herringbone Russian white oak floors throughout brightly tied all the elements together. By putting every inch of the floor plan to work, we transformed the apartment from two bedrooms to four, improved the flow, enhanced the natural light in every room, all the while maintaining the traditional elegance of the pre-war building.

properties.nom_etablissement: Studio Idaë, Vegetable Orchestra, Luchthaven Schiphol, Evert van de Beekstraat 202, 1118 CP Schiphol, Pays-Bas
properties.adresse: Luchthaven Schiphol, Evert van de Beekstraat 202, 1118 CP Schiphol, Pays-Bas
properties.description_projet: In « Vegetable Orchestra », winter vegetables transform into double bass, guitars, trumpets and xylophones and are meeting up for a concert. With chosen colors and carpet as the main material, confort and warmth are reinforced.

properties.nom_etablissement: sam baron, Signalétique Covid, Musée d'Art, Architecture et Technologie, Av. Brasília, 1300-598 Lisboa, Portugal
properties.adresse: Musée d'Art, Architecture et Technologie, Av. Brasília, 1300-598 Lisboa, Portugal
properties.description_projet: Baron created the series of interventions to allow visitors to the Amanda Levete-designed Museum of Art, Architecture and Technology (MAAT) in Lisbon to navigate the building while adhering to social distancing guidelines. "It's an ingenious, simple but very effective and fun solution that uses basic materials like bricks (in reference to the old building), mirrors and adhesive lettering and populates all spaces at strategic intersections to help people. to navigate the museum in accordance with the rules. " The signage was made using a combination of red bricks, green adhesive and mirrors (in which visitors are reflected) communicating safety information and indicating the one-way museum visit to be observed.

properties.nom_etablissement: emmanuelle moureaux architecture + design, 100 colors flowers for PATEK PHILIPPE, Sands Theatre, Marina Bay Sands, Singapore
properties.adresse: Sands Theatre, Marina Bay Sands, Singapore
properties.description_projet: After Dubai, Munich, London and New York, Singapore has been chosen by Patek Philippe as the venue for the fifth Watch Art Grand Exhibition that offered in-depth insights into its universe and its creations. Taking place during the Singapore Bicentennial year, the exhibition hosted at the Marina Bay Sands Theater was the largest to date. Collectors, aficionados of watchmaking artistry and the general public were able to immerse themselves in the world of Patek Philippe recreated in ten rooms in an exhibition of over 1800 square meters. The centerpiece “100 colors flowers”, made up of 11,500 flowers with its petals featuring 100 shades of colors welcomed visitors as they entered the first room of the exhibition, the Singapore 200th Anniversary Room. In the spirit of Majulah Singapura (the starting two words of the national anthem which captures the spirit of Singapore – onwards Singapore) the installation is inspired by the flora of this island full of colors, exuberance, vitality and life. Colorful and immersive the installation reflects how time flows gently as if the space has its own time. Inspired by the beauty, color and fragrance of frangipani flowers, this creation also reflects the beauty, spirit and dynamism of Singapore. Petals are carefully assembled by hand to form this shape which captures the spirit of nature as a master craftsman with ability to create and shape beautiful forms. The installation also captures the immense precision of Patek Philippe master craftsmen & watchmakers. Attracting 68,000 visitors over the course of 16 days, the Watch Art Grand Exhibition was the most successful to date.

properties.nom_etablissement: Aurelien Chen, Art Installation #2 for Chinese Liquor Boutique Hotel, Yan'an, Shaanxi, Chine
properties.titre_affiche: Art Installation #2 for Chinese Liquor Boutique Hotel
properties.description_projet: A sensorial journey through the making of traditional Chinese wine: alcohol fermentation stage. In China, alcohol is made from cereals seeds, following the same process for centuries. After a careful study of this process, we created a specific architectural scenography that gives the visitor the opportunity to experience the process of making Chinese wine. Outdoor spaces are part of this sensorial course, creating a continuity between interior and exterior. When entering the entrance lobby, visitor stands on a transparent carpet made of glass. Underneath lie a series of jars that are half buried, giving the illusion of ancient jars. This carpet extends to the outdoor space, reminding of traditional distilleries where so many jars were put together on the ground that they would recover the entire space and become like a carpet. At the back of the yard, the jars emerge from the ground and become a fountain. The water that runs along the ceramic emphasizes the material. Collaborator : Zhijian Workshop : Aurelien Chen (lead) + Wang Ke Yao and Jiang Ze (Landscape design)

properties.nom_etablissement: Maison Malapert, Village ClubMed de la Caravelle, Sainte-Anne, Guadeloupe
properties.description_projet: This renovation by interior designer Maison Malapert project has made the resort Club Med's new flagship in the French West Indies. The project is another instance of Club Med contributing to the development of the Guadeloupe islands and increasing the appeal of the destination to international guests. This renovated and extended resort strengthens its long-standing partnership with local stakeholders, including the municipality of Sainte Anne, and further supports the Guadeloupean economy. This investment in the resort has secured 275 jobs and created more than 100 new ones and at least the same number of indirect jobs. Club Med La Caravelle also uses approximately 10 external service providers. Club Med La Caravelle currently employs nearly 400 international and local employees, including around 270 local Guadeloupeans. Caravelle: An Ideal Destination for an International Clientele of Families and Couples Located on one of the Caribbean's most beautiful beaches, Club Med Caravelle enjoys an exceptional setting and a warm tropical climate almost all year round. The resort now offers a comprehensive range of children's clubs, including a new Baby Club (providing care and play for children from 4 months to 23 months old). The resort is particularly suitable for multi-generational families, featuring areas like the new water play park for parents and children to come together and create vacation memories to treasure. The resort's new Zen Oasis welcomes adults in search of well-being. Specifically designed for rest and relaxation, this area overlooking the sea features an infinity pool and Deluxe and Suite rooms, perfect to unwind. To extend the relaxation, adults can take advantage of bespoke spa treatments at the brand-new Club Med Spa by Sothys. Thanks to its wide range of sporting activities and water sports, Club Med Caravelle is also an ideal vacation destination for trying out different sports, discovering new passions, seeking thrills, and returning home with more than just memories. The perfect place to experience the local culture The resort's Caribbean-inspired architecture and design immerse guests in the culture of the Guadeloupe islands. In addition to the redesigned rooms, there are new Superior rooms and Suites for families offering stunning ocean views. With its new Gourmet Lounge restaurant, the Allamanda Beach Lounge, Club Med Caravelle invites guests to discover new culinary experiences in an idyllic and welcoming beachside setting. With its ever-changing all-day dining menu, customers can enjoy all the flavors of Guadeloupean cuisine, from late lunch to dinner. Guests at the resort can also discover the new wine cellar at its restaurant, L'Hibiscus.

properties.nom_etablissement: RICH DESIGNERS, ClubMed - Village de Da Balaïa, Village de Da Balaïa, Algarve, Portugal
properties.adresse: Village de Da Balaïa, Algarve, Portugal
properties.description_projet: The site is completely renovated. Our mission is to offer a set of lighting solutions that will integrate a new interior design: guest bedrooms, corridors and main entrance atrium of the Hotel Golf, Amalia Bar, Vasco de Gama restaurant, business Centre, shops, and amphitheatre. The quality of the spaces is due to the attention paid to the ambiences, comfort and functionality while considering energy issues and the economics of the project. We design a large 2.5m diameter pendant light that acts like a light trap. The chandelier emits light and reflects lights around it. Three sheets of shiny polished brass perforated and folded are superimposed. Inserted between the 2 upper sheets 13 lighting devices project a flow through the perforations of the lower sheet. The suspended assembly reflects a peripheral flow installed remotely.

properties.nom_etablissement: Living Architecture Bacin Olivier (LABO), Driggs Ave for MoMA, Museum of Modern Art, 11 W 53rd St, New York, NY 10019, États-Unis
properties.adresse: Museum of Modern Art, 11 W 53rd St, New York, NY 10019, États-Unis
properties.description_projet: For this special MoMA shop limited edition designed in Brooklyn we decided to draw a furniture line inspired by New York city and Williamsburg in particular. We got inspired by the vintage colors and materials we can find where we live, we picked felt and wood as a nice contrast of color and texture. But we also translated the facinating geometry of the industrial river crane into some triangular shapes. Then the design is thought to be sustainable, affordable and engaging with the user. So we created a flat packaging using the latest fabrication technologies (CNC) so that the user can easilly build it without any tool and we worked hard to avoid scrap of materials to reduce the cost as well as the ecological impact. The stool Driggs Ave is thought as a nice comfortable and folding stool, ideal for every place.

properties.nom_etablissement: Piergil Fourquié, Scenography for Expo 2020 Dubai, Lehbab Street - Dubai - Émirats arabes unis
properties.adresse: Lehbab Street - Dubai - Émirats arabes unis
properties.description_projet: The Dubai World Expo, from October 1, 2021 to March 31, 2022. Theme: Connecting minds, Building the future mobility, sustainability, opportunity. More than 25 million visitors are expected, 190 countries will be represented. Space: On an area of ​​1800 m², the France Pavilion will be completely removable and reusable. Temporary exhibition space: Surface area of ​​177m². The French art of living a dream to share, between dream and reality the initiatory journey of an exhibition driven by new technologies ONCE UPON A TIME, the three myths. The visitor's initiatory journey through the universe of three legendary houses, Christofle, Bernardaud, Baccarat, which have forever marked the French art of living. To rediscover the lost magic through the scenography, to accept the improbable and the marvelous.

properties.nom_etablissement: Atelier Cedric Breisacher, SCALES Divided, Walker Tower, 212 W 18th St, New York, NY 10011, États-Unis
properties.adresse: Walker Tower, 212 W 18th St, New York, NY 10011, États-Unis
properties.description_projet: SCALES is a collection of large-scale pieces. First presented at the Collectible fair in Brussels in 2020. The table was made from a single plane wood top. For the Walker Tower exhibition, the table has been split in two to facilitate its installation. A three-metre table fits into a box half the size. More than a logistical advantage, it is also a concrete response to energy savings in the transport of large-scale works.

properties.nom_etablissement: CHARLES KALKAPIAN, Mirage - Paravent, Hotel Le Meridien Riyadh, Ibn Abdulaziz Road, Al Woroud District, King Abdullah, Riyadh 11544, Arabie saoudite
properties.adresse: Hotel Le Meridien Riyadh, Ibn Abdulaziz Road, Al Woroud District, King Abdullah, Riyadh 11544, Arabie saoudite
properties.description_projet: This full and delicate calligraphy draws the dunes of the golden desert and the urbanization of Riyadh, the capital that continues to metamorphose. The Mirage screen is an invitation to travel through the manual work of brass and metal, creating a dialogue between space and man. It will be installed in front of the large glass walls of the Royal Suite in Le Meridien.

properties.nom_etablissement: Philippe Rahm Architectes, Taichung Central Park , Taïchung, Taïwan
properties.description_projet: The urban principle of structuring the park is based on variations in gradations of climatic ambiences, between existing areas that are warmer, wetter, more polluted, and new areas that are created, cooler, less humid, less polluted. Starting from the existing areas, we define three climate maps, each one for a specific atmospheric parameter: a map for heat, a map describing the variations in air humidity and a last map describing the intensity of air pollution.

properties.nom_etablissement: Atelier du Pont, Repossi Dubai, Dubai Mall, Financial Center Street, Along Sheikh Zayed Road, Next to Burj Khalifa - Dubai - Émirats arabes unis
properties.adresse: Dubai Mall, Financial Center Street, Along Sheikh Zayed Road, Next to Burj Khalifa - Dubai - Émirats arabes unis
properties.description_projet: Founded in Turin in 1920, Repossi has since become established across the globe. New corners and boutiques respect the brand’s DNA and its heritage of several generations of jewelers. A new design is created for each site based on an exacting use of materials, a dialogue between transparent and opaque volumes, and an interplay of matte and reflective surfaces through the use of tinted mirrors, of shiny and brushed copper and moiré carpeting. The triangular shape is echoed and reinterpreted in the store windows and the pleated, shiny, dazzling, and precious jewelry boxes.

properties.nom_etablissement: ciguë, % ARABICA DUMBO, 20 Old Fulton St, Brooklyn, NY 11201, États-Unis
properties.adresse: 20 Old Fulton St, Brooklyn, NY 11201, États-Unis
properties.description_projet: Work in progress project We were asked to design the first %Arabica coffee shop In New York City, at the emblematic and culturally rich DUMBO* neighborhood in Brooklynn district. (*acronym of Down Under the Manhattan Bridge Overpass) The location favors a wide view of the Brooklyn bridge, East River and the island of Manhattan. The store was to house a Probat Coffee Roaster, a beautiful piece of craftsmanship manufactured by hand since 1920. The layout of the workspace is articulated around the Probat which is surrounded by the different counter and a bean cellar in the back. A ten meters counter precedes the workspace, fully clad in vibrated aluminum. On the top of it is featured a seven meters lamp built in blown glass and brass (exclusive collaboration ciguë x Viabizzuno). Reclaimed wood floor and red brick cladding contrasts with the aluminium counters and the exposed technical ceiling, as a collage, these elements refer to Brooklyn's industrial past and the hustle and bustle of the New York of today.

properties.nom_etablissement: Elliott Barnes Interiors, Urban Narratives - Toranomon Show Case Apartment, Toranomon, Tokyo, Japon
properties.titre_affiche: Urban Narratives - Toranomon Show Case Apartment
properties.description_projet: Elevated living is a particular lifestyle because of the vantage point offered. An imaginary promenade between the heavens and the earth, allows one to appreciate different terrestrial sceneries and enjoy a more expansive connection to the sky. The view is filled with multiple references that blend together in a kaleidoscope of changing dreamlike urban impressions. As a result different almost surrealistic narratives come together to make a living environment that is amusing and unique.

properties.nom_etablissement: Charles Zana, Appartement Champel, Champel, Avenue de Champel 10, 1206 Genève, Suisse
properties.adresse: Champel, Avenue de Champel 10, 1206 Genève, Suisse
properties.description_projet: The renovation and extension of this single-story apartment in Geneva were designed as a convivial house. The living rooms on the first floor are wide open and offer direct access to the private garden on three sides. In the basement, the building has relaxation areas: spa, pool, and cinema. Surface: 750 m2

properties.nom_etablissement: Caron & Associés, Penthouse Hôtel 5 étoiles The Chedi Andermatt, The Chedi Residences, Gotthardstrasse 4, 6490 Andermatt, Suisse
properties.titre_affiche: Penthouse Hôtel 5 étoiles The Chedi Andermatt
properties.adresse: The Chedi Residences, Gotthardstrasse 4, 6490 Andermatt, Suisse
properties.description_projet: In the heart of an exceptional natural setting in the Swiss Alps, creation of a luxury penthouse with generous volumes open to nature. Opting for a contemporary and warm design, this project is a tribute to the environment that surrounds it through a selection of materials and details echoing stones, forests and ice. The crest line of the surrounding peaks is also integrated into a line of brass inlaid in a herringbone parquet floor that follows its shape.

properties.nom_etablissement: Caprini Pellerin Architectes, Dinnes, Brandstätte 10, 1010 Wien, Autriche
properties.description_projet: Caprini & Pellerin Architectes is a Cannes based practice established in 2008, working internationally on luxury residential and commercial projects. The practice was founded by two raw talents: Kevin Caprini and Jerry Pellerin. The practice has since established a reputation for delivering outstanding turn-key designs from concept through to completion. The two architects lead a growing team of over twenty designers, architects and consultants, sharing a broad range of interlocking skills. This gives them the opportunity to embrace every aspect of architectural, interior and landscape design. Suited to both traditional and modern architecture, Caprini & Pellerin Architectes deliver an avant-garde vision of luxury, which they believe is achieved through meticulous focus on detail, made to measure fittings, characterful materials, collaborating closely with each client. The two architects draw their creativity from the constraints of each project. They have signed off a diverse portfolio of properties around the world spanning from elegant Provençal Bastides, to minimalist contemporary houses, all the way to luxury hotels and mountain chalets.

properties.nom_etablissement: Chzon, Hôtel Menorca, Menorca, Spain
properties.adresse: Menorca Experimental, Batería Militar de Llucalari, Camí de Llucalari, 07730 Alaior, Illes Balears, Espagne
properties.description_projet: Menorca experimental is a 30ha property near alaior in menorca that was thought as being the summer residence of an imaginary artist. As mirò did with majorca, dali with cadaquès, picasso on the french riviera, le corbusier in roquebrune st martin... So dedicated to drawing, meditating, loosing time, music, swimming, contemplation, sunset watching… thanks to the amazing landscape. The overall aesthetic of the hotel was made to get inspired. Dorothee meilichzon & team starting point for the project was to infuse some of the menorcan savoir faire and materials : stones, concrete built furniture, terra cotta, half circled shapes, architraves, wood shutters, leather, recycled materials from the former farms : wooden beams, roof tiles and marres stones. Together with very unique details and drawings : colored shaped door’s architraves, round shaped concrete beadheads and vanities, colorfull palettes of cement and lacquer, terracotta and glazed handmade tiles. Furniture were built by locals artisans of the island following dorothee’s drawing.

properties.nom_etablissement: Maison Numéro 20, Penthouse UK, London, Royaume-Uni
properties.description_projet: Behind the facade of this old London building, hides a penthouse of 350 m2 . French chic and daring have been the guiding thread of this London apartment where contemporary art dominates (Yves Klein, Man Ray, Soulage). A true mix and match of motif, material, art and style. A 1930s folding screen gives presence to the space and echoes the plant table in the manner of Lalanne, the carpets in shades of silk animate the floor.

properties.nom_etablissement: Frédéric Saulou, Walker Tower project, Walker Tower, 212 W 18th St, New York, NY 10011, États-Unis
properties.adresse: Walker Tower, 212 W 18th St, New York, NY 10011, États-Unis
properties.description_projet: The Walker Tower project is an interior design project sponsored by the Franco-American gallery, Galerie Philia, whose showroom is based in NY. Initially, the project was to put in t abyss of a show apartment, it were then acquired by a private client with all the furniture. The furnishings has been composed of soft and raw materials both to contrast with the upscale environment of the place. Furniture : Low table in Bourgogne limestone (FR) and patinated brass, Brut Mirror in Trélazé Slate (FR) et lacquered mirror, Sculpted side Table in Buffon marble limestone (FR)

properties.nom_etablissement: Emmanuelle Moureaux Architecture + Design, 100 Colors No.31, Kumamoto-jo Hall, 3-40 Sakuramachi, Chuo Ward, Kumamoto, 860-0805, Japon
properties.adresse: Kumamoto-jo Hall, 3-40 Sakuramachi, Chuo Ward, Kumamoto, 860-0805, Japon
properties.description_projet: Special installation for the opening of Kumamoto-Jo hall in collaboration with the Contemporary Art Museum, Kumamoto. The installation visualizes the future 100 years from 2019 to 2118. About the "100 colors" series "100 colors" is an installation series began in 2013, which forms space using 100 shades of colors. Emmanuelle wishes to give emotions through colors as she felt from seeing overflowing "colors" in Tokyo when she first visited in 1995. She also wishes to give opportunities for people to see, touch and feel colors with their senses to become more conscious of colors that exist around them. In "100 colors", Colors are explored in various forms depending on the environment, to maximize the beauty of colors. 100 colors entering the body with a glance triggers a physical response to engage with the sensation of colors. The installation series will continue to travel around the world.

properties.nom_etablissement: Aurelien Chen, Art Installation #1 for Chinese Liquor Boutique Hotel, Yan'an, Shaanxi, Chine
properties.titre_affiche: Art Installation #1 for Chinese Liquor Boutique Hotel
properties.description_projet: A sensorial journey through the making of traditional Chinese wine. Last stage of the process : steaming and condensation. In China, alcohol is made from cereals seeds, following the same process for centuries. After a careful study of this process, we created a specific architectural scenography that gives the visitor the opportunity to experience the process of making Chinese wine. Outdoor spaces are part of this sensorial course, creating a continuity between interior and exterior. The installation located in the main courtyard reminds the transformation of liquid, from steam to condensation in drop of alcohol. It is a monumental jar. Yet, it is delicately floating between ground floor and basement. It becomes a landmark, highly visible from every interior space, especially from the labyrinthine basement. Steam goes out from the upper part of the gigantic jar, then drops run down the stainless steel bars, and end up in a perfect circle at the ground. Collaborator : Zhijian Workshop : Aurelien Chen (lead) + Wang Ke Yao and Jiang Ze (Landscape design)

properties.nom_etablissement: Atelier Donatien Carratier, So Sofitel, Hua Hin, Province de Prachuap Khiri Khan 77110, Thaïlande
properties.adresse: Hua Hin, Province de Prachuap Khiri Khan 77110, Thaïlande
properties.description_projet: Painting the canvas is Donatien Carratier, who brings to the new resort over 20 years of design experience in Asia. The forward-thinking interior designer, who focuses on luxury projects that demand iconic styling, is famed for creating deeply resonant environments in which vivid dreams blur with reality. Drawing inspiration from the Grand Gallerie de l'Evolution natural history museum in Paris, he is the visionary behind SO Sofitel Hua Hin's 'Evolution of Life' theme, which begins with friendly animal statues that greet guests on arrival and proceeds to wild animal sculptures around the reflecting pond and rabbits, inspire from Lexis Carroll hiding throughout the resort, literally putting a whimsical surprise around every corner. For the private spaces, Donatien developed two vibrant room styles: SO Nature and SO Arty.

properties.nom_etablissement: Aw², Kasiiya Papagayo, Kasiiya Papagayo, Costa Rica
properties.description_projet: Eco-lodge: 14 tents, restaurant, beach club, communal spaces Kasiiya is not a hotel. Kasiiya is part of nature. Built on timber platforms from natural materials, it leaves no scar on its landscape. From the very beginning, the conservation of the tropical forest has been paramount. Our intention throughout the project was not to have minimal impact on the environment, but zero. This project in Costa Rica has propelled architecture and the boutique hotel experience into a new dimension, or one might say, a new ecology. Architecture and nature can live in symbiosis rather than in opposition, without one trying to gain ground over the other.Kasiiya is the application of this concept. The project was completed without cutting down a single tree and without the use of concrete and nails. Meticulously positioned amidst 123 acres of wild landscape, our concept stems from the idea that there should be no frontier between architecture and the surrounding wilderness, between the inside and the outside. This Kasiiya Papagayo is composed on the scale of a village, made up of clusters of tents, densifying the habitat in some areas and then letting nature take full rein in others. Constructed from mainly local natural materials, each tent offers its guests total comfort with bespoke furniture designed by AW². Each tent is carefully orientated to reconnect with nature alone. Inside the tents, the camping mindset continues. The demountable character of the tentes, which makes it possible at any time to make the place the same as on arrival, is what gives this project this eco-responsible aspect.

properties.nom_etablissement: Pierre-Yves Rochon, Four Seasons Florence, Borgo Pinti, 99, 50121 Firenze FI, Italie
properties.description_projet: The meticulous seven-year restoration of a converted 15th century palace and 16th century convent blend modern comforts with original Italian Renaissance architectural elements. Frescoes, paintings, bronze sculptures, mosaics, moldings and stained glass offer a unique glimpse into the rich history of Florence throughout the hotel’s public areas, 116 guestrooms and 4 restaurants. Surrounding the Palazzo della Gherardesca, the Giardina della Gherardesca is one of the largest gardens in Florence and an urban green sanctuary for the hotel.

properties.nom_etablissement: Wilmotte & Associés, Glass Chamber of the "Operation Night Watch", Rijksmuseum, Museumstraat 1, 1071 XX Amsterdam, Pays-Bas
properties.titre_affiche: Glass Chamber of the "Operation Night Watch", Rijksmuseum
properties.description_projet: Six years after having redesigned the interior architecture and the museography of the Rijksmuseum’s exhibition galleries, one of the most beautiful European museum, Jean-Michel Wilmotte has created for “Operation Night Watch” -project of restauration of Rembrandt’s master piece - an ultra-transparent glass chamber, which allows to the public to follow in full view its study and revival. This glass chamber is made of 21 glass panels with an identical size (95 x 400 cm) in order to allow the replacement of a panel in case of a broken glass.

properties.nom_etablissement: Frédéric Saulou, Moving Traces, Burgstraat, 9000 Gent, Belgique
properties.description_projet: Installation of furniture for a private client's salon in Ghent. The marriage of natural and raw materials is the guiding line of this tailor-made project. Furniture: Black slate sideboard with patinated and engraved brass, black slate mirror and gray smoked mirror.

properties.nom_etablissement: Maison Numéro 20, Villa Cielo, Ibiza, Eivissa, 07800, Baléares, Espagne
properties.description_projet: Villa Cielo is an elegant and refined summer house in ibiza. It offers a breathtaking view of the Mediterranean Sea. Immaculate in white, blue and gold, Villa Cielo represents a vibrant mix of sophisticated casual. The blue is there to honor, going from indigo, to klein blue or turquoise as an echo to the sky and the sea. This former Finca revisited called upon the talents of French craftsmen (painter decorator, layout artist and editor, landscape architect) and benefited from a complete interior and exterior restructuring.

properties.nom_etablissement: Ludovic Roth, Clarks Originals Design Studio, Somerset, Royaume-Uni

The project integrates the conception of various zones and the design of furniture such as desks, meeting table, trolleys, shelves, shoe wall, closets...

properties.nom_etablissement: Eric Prigent Bespoke Design, Maison Camus Lounge Beijing, Reignwood Center, 8 Yong'an Dongli, Jianguomenwai Dajie. Chaoyang District
properties.adresse: Reignwood Center, 8 Yong'an Dongli, Jianguomenwai Dajie. Chaoyang District

Vistas and circulations have been at the forefront of the design in order to form an elegant flow between rooms and spaces; small to large, dark to light in to create an inherent sense of drama and understated opulence. properties.nom_etablissement: Frédéric Saulou, Tribeca Residence, New York, Etats-Unis
properties.description_projet: Creation of a tailor-made table for a private client appartement and commissioned by the interior design studio The Prestige Group. Central element of the dining room, the client wanted a large black table in French stone. Slate dining table from Trélazé (FR)

properties.nom_etablissement: Studio Catoir, Penthouse Italy, Saronno, 21047 Varèse, Italie

Studio Catoir were given carte blanche with the design and aesthetic of the apartment. properties.nom_etablissement: Atelier Du Pont, Boutique Burma, Dubai Mall, Financial Center Street, Along Sheikh Zayed Road, Next to Burj Khalifa - Dubai - Émirats arabes unis
properties.adresse: Dubai Mall, Financial Center Street, Along Sheikh Zayed Road, Next to Burj Khalifa - Dubai - Émirats arabes unis
properties.description_projet: Located at the famous Fashion Avenue in the Dubai Mall, this precisely and soberly designed boutique creates an exceptional environment for viewing jewelry that suits the brand’s image. Suspended elliptical showcases, alluring and ethereal, populate the shop’s monumental windows. The boutique is characterized by an interplay of curves of lacquered perforated metal running from floor to ceiling that provides visitors with a sense of softness. The space is divided into several small private showrooms and alcoves that provide a more intimate environment for presenting unique pieces.

properties.nom_etablissement: Charles Zana, Comptoir Goyard Bergdof-Goodman, Comptoir Goyard Bergdof-Goodman, 18 Highland Park Village, Dallas, TX 75205, Etats-Unis
properties.adresse: Comptoir Goyard Bergdof-Goodman, 18 Highland Park Village, Dallas, TX 75205, Etats-Unis
