properties.nom_etablissement: Atelier Cedric Breisacher, Dot (Chair), Bruxelles, Belgique
properties.description_projet: The Dot collection continues the minimalist research initiated by the Shave series. How to draw a chair with as few lines as possible? The design is returned to its essentials, six wooden battens structure the seat, then this structure is sculpted so as to only reveal the lines of the seat and the base. Integrated into a local production process, the oak comes from northern forests and the assembly parts are designed to be produced in CNC.

properties.nom_etablissement: Philippe Rahm Architectes, Munchen Bleibt Cool / Masterplan Pour Munich Nord_Est, Munich, Allemagne
properties.titre_affiche: Munchen Bleibt Cool / Masterplan Pour Munich Nord_Est
properties.description_projet: The purpose of the competition is to propose a master plan for the huge urban development of the city of Munich in Germany, by studying 3 scenarios, to accommodate 10000, 2000 or 30000 new inhabitants. Our proposal takes into account wind as a fundamental means of evacuating the accumulation of heat during hot summer periods and that of fine particles. In this way, real rivers of air are preserved while the built-up areas are densified by extending the existing hamlets.

properties.nom_etablissement: Julie Conrad, CEGO, 5 Av. des Hauts-Fourneaux, 4362 Esch-sur-Alzette, Luxembourg
properties.description_projet: Competition winner 2021: Interior Design Category of the Circular by design challenge by Luxinnovation & the Creative Industries Cluster CEGO is a circular space-saving furniture system for reasonably priced housing. We apply circular design principles to housing in order to optimise and diversify space use and make housing affordable while maintaining high living standards. Offered to tenants as part of the rental scheme, this concealed furniture uses locally sourced fibreboards and covers valuable functions in the home. Replacing big pieces of furniture, it is there when needed and disappears when it is not. CEGO will be integrated into housing build by PROgroup starting at the end of 2021 / beginning of 2022.

properties.nom_etablissement: Nazak Design, Susan Falk, The Hamptons, État de New York, États-Unis
properties.adresse: The Hamptons, État de New York, États-Unis
properties.description_projet: This project began in 2018 when a New York City couple approached me to help reimagine their traditional/classic cottage in Amagansett, among the most rustic and authentic of the “Hamptons” areas in Long Island. Built in 1998, the home was intended to fit seamlessly into the local architectural style. This traditional style served the family well as the children grew up. But with the kids now out on their own, the couple wanted to update their home in anticipation of a new phase in life and a more contemporary lifestyle. The clients flirted with the idea of starting from scratch, finding land and building, but ultimately determined that the home’s location and views — just a stone’s throw from untamed Atlantic beaches —could not be replicated. So we decided to undertake a ground-up rebuild. And we’d have to do it fast—the client did not want to miss even a single summer. That left us about eight months, from October to May, to complete the renovation. The challenge was to create a more open flow in the interiors adding increased light and airiness and taking advantage of the home’s privileged seaside location. Unnecessary doors closed off the public/entertaining rooms downstairs;thresholds were low and narrow, and some rooms were barely used. With these obstacles removed and reconfigured, a new and easy flow emerged. The furniture were sourced through local or international vendors, auction houses, with a mix of contemporary and vintage. Upstairs where the family bedrooms were situated needed more dramatic updating. We needed to rethink the entire floor plan. Five small bedrooms were transformed to three generous ones, each with an ensuite bathroom. The master bedroom was doubled in size and moved to the front of the house to take advantage of the ocean views. A double door would separate their bedroom with the en suite bathroom and walk in closet for a desired privacy. Their daughters’ rooms, at the opposite end of the hallway, were enlarged and en suite bathrooms were added. Removing one bedroom and repurposing the space as a cozy sitting room (with fireplace) was a bonus. And having the plumbing lines and a corner space, we added a full bath in case of unexpected guests! Then we had to address the connective tissue, where upstairs meets downstairs. The landing at the top of the stairs was reconfigured into an open library with floor to ceiling bookcases and seating. Perhaps the real coup was converting a portion of the attic into an open air patio area with broad water views. To access the space via the central staircase beginning on the ground level, we designed a wood and steel railing which zigzags up to the third floor. The key to our successful outcome was our close collaboration, listening, flexibility and patience. The ultimate sign that the approach worked? Our delighted clients can’t spend enough time in their new space.

properties.nom_etablissement: Julie Conrad, Is(o)lands, Luxembourg
properties.description_projet: A flexible and mobile scenography for 8 different Covid-19-related plays, articulated around 3 themes: [1] offer a platform to discuss the state of emergency [2] create a hymn to the forgotten of the crisis [3] make an inventory of beautiful things. - Competition winner - https://jcds.lu/isolands

properties.nom_etablissement: Raphael Navot, Aleatoric, 515 W 26th St, New York, NY 10001, États-Unis
properties.adresse: 515 W 26th St, New York, NY 10001, États-Unis
properties.description_projet: Patchwork assembly of arbitrary massive pieces of sand-blasted aged oak. The piece is combining the ancient method ‘Mortise and Tenon’ which is dating back 7000 years together with contemporary technique of 5 axis robotics. Both simple and strong, the organic pieces are hand joined to lock the different fibre direction into a fortified composition. This piece is made in France and is a part of a limited edition series commissioned by Friedman Benda gallery in New York.

properties.nom_etablissement: Suduca & Merillou, Casa de Pinheiros, Comporta, Portugal
properties.description_projet: It's on a dune near Lisbon, in a very posh gypset area, that Suduca & Merillou built this vacation house. Inspired by the houses of local fisherlmen, they designed a set of 5 cabanas , one for the living room, one for the kitchen and the others for bedrooms. They used traditional local materials: straw, wood, bamboo, lime ,to create a pure, simplerelaxing atmosphere.

properties.nom_etablissement: Lina Ghotmeh—Architecture, Stone Garden, Beyrouth, Liban
properties.description_projet: Located in the port area of Beirut, « Stone Garden » takes its roots from its context. Appearing in the city as an earthly emergence, its custom-designed and hand-combed by artisans. It portrays the capacity of architecture to act as a healing tool and build resilience at times of crisis. The tower appears as a sculpture drawn on an urban scale.

properties.nom_etablissement: Roxane Lahidji, Nimbus, 86-88 Pimlico Road, London SW1W 8PL
properties.description_projet: Large living room coffee table in marbled salts and inspired by aerial landscapes.

properties.nom_etablissement: Philippe Rahm Architectes, Limpidarium, San Cristoforo, Milan, Italie
properties.description_projet: The environmental strategy behind the 2 new masterplans on 2 former railway wastelands in Milan is to first set up two environmental filters (Limpidarium), one cleaning the air at Farini, i.e. an 18-hectare park filtering the hot and polluted air coming with the prevailing wind from the South-West to the South-East, and the other of 15 hectares cleaning the water at San Cristoforo to produce a natural swimming pool. The volumetry of the new district in Farini lets the refreshing convective winds pass through, avoiding the accumulation of fine polluting particles. Urban development can be carried out quietly over 50 years, without depending on a minimum investment. Urban planning regulations are based on albedo, absence of light pollution, amplification of ecological corridors.

properties.nom_etablissement: Jacques Garcia, Vertigo, Al Khaleej St, Doha, Qatar
properties.description_projet: Open Sky, Shining Stars Located on level 28, Vertigo Doha is one of the highest lounges in the Mushaireb area with incredible 360-degree views of Doha’s Skyline, Corniche and old city. Vertigo offers an experience like no other with a creative beverages menu, mixology inventions and Pan-Asian cuisine with a Mediterranean twist in a lively set up with music.

properties.nom_etablissement: Saguez & Partners, Stazione de Milano Centrale, Piazza Duca d'Aosta, 20124 Milan, Italie
properties.description_projet: Milano Centrale is THE Milanese train station. It is the heart of the city, with 120M passengers walking through its halls every years. It is the starting point of a great escapade in Como’s Lake for the WE. It is the destination of foreign visitors arriving for the Design's and Fashion's weeks. And it is also an events place with fashions shows, pop-up for the launchings of new products and other happenings. Milano Centrale embodies the Milanese Chic, the Italian lifestyle and the modernity of the city. Saguez&Partners gives it a new energy with a carefully crafted intervention : opening of the station using indoors/outdoors Dolce Vita terraces, welcoming of new delicious concepts such as the Mercato Centrale di Milano or highlighting of the fashion shops with brass arches. Passengers are not forgotten with improved intuitive circulations and seatings redesigned with new uses in the main hall. Milan's heart is beating stronger, giving the pulse of the Lombardian’s capitale.

properties.nom_etablissement: Arnaud Lapierre, Fractal, Shanghai, Chine
properties.description_projet: Commissioned by the city of Shanghai, this installation, 5 meters high and 15 m wide, allows visitors and residents of the neighborhood to take a stride over the water and feel the shimmering sensation of water. An unstructured walk to create a meeting point that symbolizes the neighborhood.

properties.nom_etablissement: Désormeaux/Carrette, Vis à vis: between art and design, Chine, Guangdong Province, Shenzhen, Futian District, 中心城福中路184号 邮政编码: 518000
properties.titre_affiche: Vis à vis: between art and design
properties.adresse: Chine, Guangdong Province, Shenzhen, Futian District, 中心城福中路184号 邮政编码: 518000
properties.description_projet: Vis à vis presents an emerging generation of designers through an exhibition path that gradually industrial, editorial, conceptual and technological approaches of the different designers…’ stated Döppel Studio and Désormeaux/Carrette. ‘A generation of designers to closely follow'

properties.nom_etablissement: Döppel Studio, Vis à vis: between art and design, Chine, Guangdong Province, Shenzhen, Futian District, 中心城福中路184号 邮政编码: 518000
properties.titre_affiche: Vis à vis: between art and design
properties.adresse: Chine, Guangdong Province, Shenzhen, Futian District, 中心城福中路184号 邮政编码: 518000
properties.description_projet: Project in collaboration with the Desormeaux / Carrette studio Installation Vis à vis: between art and design, between France and China Döppel Studio, the French Designer firm from Paris, represented by Jonathan Omar and Lionel Dinis-Salazar was among the 16 French designers studios gathered at the Design Week of Shenzhen on the theme of “sustainability”. Scenographers but also exhibitors, they collaborate with Nathanaël Désormeaux and Damien Carrette, representatives of Desormeaux / Carrette studio. This quartet of emerging French designers has decided to combine their expertise to enhance this project. This approach is seen as a meeting between industrial design (Désormeaux / Carrette) and the plastic & conceptual expertise of space (Döppel studio). Creating a scenography with a new vocabulary, between technical and conceptual part, came as an evidence. The exhibition « Vis à vis : entre art et design, entre France et Chine « invite this heritage as a basement of contemporary creations. The scenographic elements of the exhibition translate this intangible heritage into ghost-like steles. This minimal scenography becomes sophisticated by materiality: lights, transparencies, ghost apparitions and reflections allow a dialogue between all the elements of this exhibition. This installation raise the lights of the past as pillars of future creations.

properties.nom_etablissement: Humbert & Poyet, Aquazzura, 939 Madison Ave, New York, NY 10021, États-Unis
properties.adresse: 939 Madison Ave, New York, NY 10021, États-Unis
properties.description_projet: Emil Humbert and Christophe Poyet pictured this space as a theatrical setting, combining striking graphics and elegant design elements. The deep shades of blue, green, purple and pink inspired by Dorothy Draper's color scheme, allow the grand columns and arches to stand out and add to the enchanting, theatrical motif of the luxurious boutique.

properties.nom_etablissement: Chzon, Il Palazzo Experimental, Fondamenta Zattere Al Ponte Lungo, 1411, 30123 Venezia VE, Italie
properties.adresse: Fondamenta Zattere Al Ponte Lungo, 1411, 30123 Venezia VE, Italie
properties.description_projet: We have worked on the interior of the hotel and the restaurant, using very classical venetian elements that we love, but also by using more contemporary elements such as tribute to the memphis movement, some bright colors, brushed aluminum, scalloped edges, glass lamps from luciano vistosi, breccia capraia marbles, arches on bathtub.

properties.nom_etablissement: Studio Jean-Marc Gady, Stand Montblanc (Salon international de la Haute Horlogerie de Genève), Genève, Suisse
properties.titre_affiche: Stand Montblanc (Salon international de la Haute Horlogerie de Genève)
properties.description_projet: Every year during Salon International de la Haute Horlogerie, Montblanc present their latest watch collections. For the 4th scenography on SIHH Fair for Montblanc, Studio Jean-Marc Gady pays homage to the spirit of exploration and the rich tradition of the Minerva manufacture with a space dedicated to the wonder and beauty of the great outdoors. Visitors are transported to a lush expanse surrounded by breathtaking views of mountains and valleys. As soon as they enter the lobby, visitors are instantly immersed in the world of Montblanc’s latest watch collections. Pairing khaki and bronze with great elegance, the new timepieces were presented in glass, wood and aged-brass display cases laid out around a central space. Plant-laden walls framed wooden seats that invited visitors to soak up the calm and serenity of the space, enhanced by the mist of a waterfall.

properties.nom_etablissement: matali crasset, Power Station of Art's Library, 200 Hua Yuan Gang Lu, 周家渡 Huangpu Qu, Shanghai, Chine, 200231
properties.adresse: 200 Hua Yuan Gang Lu, 周家渡 Huangpu Qu, Shanghai, Chine, 200231
properties.annee_projet: Work in progress
properties.description_projet: Power Station of Art is more than a layout, it’s a dynamic system which attracts toward itself. It is a singularity hub and, in the meantime, a diffuser throughout the building. The ring is the device’s epicenter. First, it represents the openness on the margins and the emergent cultures. It pools books coming from outside. Then, this ring appears as the sign of mobility. As a railroad it has its own dynamic. Finally that shape resonate with the rest of the museum architecture.

properties.nom_etablissement: Jakob+Macfarlane, Urban Theatre, Huai Hai Zhong Lu 99, Huangpu District, Shanghai, China
properties.adresse: Huai Hai Zhong Lu 99, Huangpu District, Shanghai, China
properties.description_projet: The project was imagined as an urban theatre for a vibrant shopping area. The long storefront reveals the multi-layered interior; the side facade evokes the views from a theatre backstage. Like an interior street, the ground floor runs along a major boulevard and is equally suited for hosting défilés and displaying merchandise. A repeating structural module creates unique settings within the larger space of the store and forms a unifying framework for stairs, changing rooms and display systems.

properties.nom_etablissement: Fritsch-Durisotti, Ôzento, France / International
properties.description_projet: Ôzento is an unprecedented habitat model taking the form of a panoramic loft placed in a wilderness setting. Lasting, immersive and not intrusive, the Ôzento concept promises a life experience in harmony with its environment. It is an elegant response, in vogue, to the desire for nature combined with respect for the biotope. Discover online: www.ozento.com and sow wherever “project” rimes with “life”.

properties.nom_etablissement: LUX, L’étoile, Linköping, Sweden
properties.description_projet: This light art installation suggests to come back to the primary stage of light. It is an object to contemplate, to stargaze, as we look at the sky. Stars have always guided humans. The sun we see rising in the east and sleeping in the west, punctuates our lives. The movement of the stars is not immediately perceptible but looking at the sky for several hours during the same night, we observe that the celestial sphere turns on itself. This time, the monumental light installation is on a base on the ground, closer to visitors and proposed dynamique animations.

properties.nom_etablissement: LUX, L’étoile, Kongens Nytorv, Copenhague, Danemark
properties.description_projet: For the first time, LUX is exhibited a new version of its Light sculpture: a brand new structure, the same shape but technologically innovative LEDs. The project, commissioned by the Institut Français du Danemark and French Embassy is presenting L’ETOILE, a 3-D light art installation in the city center of Copenhagen during 3 weeks. This outdoor installation sets out to recreate that bright spot in the night sky that man has observed for millennia: the star. It represents the first and only light source visible to humans, a primary and fundamental light source. The light object, minimalist and technically innovative, offers 360° lighting and invites visitors to return to the fundamentals of light taking them as close as possible to a star to contemplate its brilliance ; Its sparkling branches seem to merge or multiply depending on where they stand.

properties.nom_etablissement: Sybille de Margerie, Four Seasons Canal Resort Residences, Dubai, Émirats arabes unis
properties.description_projet: Four Seasons Serviced Residences, 33 apartments, from 100 to 350 sqm 5 townhouses Public areas : lobby, lounge, spa

properties.nom_etablissement: Anthony Guerrée, Albertine, 241 Church St, New York, NY 10013, États-Unis
properties.adresse: 241 Church St, New York, NY 10013, États-Unis
properties.description_projet: Inspired by Albertine, famous character of In Search of Lost time. the Pomare chair takes its name and origin from the last dynasty of Tahiti’s kings. Anthony Guerrée was inspired by this high-backed chair because it symbolizes romantic desire. This chair entered popular culture in the 70’s after it was featured in the poster of the erotic film “Emmanuelle” and evokes lightness and liberal mores.

properties.nom_etablissement: LUX, L’étoile, Dubai Design District, Dubai, Émirats arabes unis
properties.adresse: Dubai Design District, Dubai, Émirats arabes unis
properties.description_projet: Inspired by space and sky, LUX sets out to recreate that bright spot in the night sky that man has observed for millennia: the star. It represents the first and only light source visible to humans, a primary and fundamental light source. Taking up the symbolic figure of this discreet star, LUX designs a gigantic 3D star with sparkling branches illuminating in cold white. With this innovative and monumental luminaire, LUX transcends the boundaries between design, digital art and micro-architecture by rethinking the different elements that make up our environments: objects, spaces, lights and decoration. The light sculpture L’ETOILE at the center of the scenography of the exhibition DESIGN AND SPACE EXPLORATION invites visitors to contemplation accompanying their journey through the other artworks with different sequences and light animations.

properties.nom_etablissement: Christopher Santerre, Moonbikes, 210 Rte des Plans, 74170 Saint-Gervais-les-Bains
properties.description_projet: Ultra-light electric snow vehicle. Brand values and product aesthetic definition. Design of two versions for mass market and one for professional in collaboration with company’s engineers.

properties.nom_etablissement: Thierry Lemaire, Villa Cologny, Lac Léman
properties.description_projet: In this spectacular villa, spaces are flooded with natural light from large bay windows. It is therefore a cube of 2000 square meters that Thierry Lemaire was entrusted with, who played marbles, wood panels, and furniture in precious wood, bronzes and other brass. He also designed most of the furniture in this project. A style review that demonstrates the agency's creative latitude.

properties.nom_etablissement: Tristan Auer, Island Shangri-La, Hong Kong
properties.description_projet: Island Shangri La is an hotel located on the island of Hong Kong. This hotel is the very first landmark of the group opened 25 years ago. IZEU studio has endeavored, through the different types of rooms, to highlight the incredible views over the bay of HK or the Peak jungle. Mix of elegance, refinement, comfort, this revival brings a modernity to accommodation while keeping the historicity of this Hong Kong figure.

properties.nom_etablissement: Xavier Cartron, Qasr Al Watan, Al Ras Al Akhdar - Abu Dhabi - Émirats arabes unis
properties.adresse: Al Ras Al Akhdar - Abu Dhabi - Émirats arabes unis
properties.description_projet: The new Presidential Palace in Abu Dhabi is one of the most prestigious building in the UAE that is utilized to house the offices of heads of states and officials as well as shall host visiting state dignitaries. The development is built on a 150 Ha Plot with a built-up area exceeding 380,000 m2. Xavier Cartron had the privilege to be part of this prestigious project’s development where the Agency was commissioned to Design and Supervise the Construction of more than 80,000 m2 of VIP and Official Areas within the Palace Complex. Xavier Cartron with its inhouse rich mix of expertise were part of developing an Individual Design Style for the Project. A style that respects the authentic Arabic-Islamic Style, yet a Mix with many classic styles that set the foundation of the innovative end product.

properties.nom_etablissement: Stephane Parmentier, The Webster, 1759 S Jameson Ln, Montecito, CA 93108, États-Unis
properties.adresse: 1759 S Jameson Ln, Montecito, CA 93108, États-Unis

properties.nom_etablissement: Studio Adrien Gardère, The Forest (Swedish Pavilion at Expo 2020 Dubai), Dubai Exhibition Centre, Dubaï, Émirats arabes unis
properties.titre_affiche: The Forest (Swedish Pavilion at Expo 2020 Dubai)
properties.adresse: Dubai Exhibition Centre, Dubaï, Émirats arabes unis
properties.description_projet: In collaboration with Alessandro Ripellino Arkitekter and Luigi Pardo Architetti, Studio Adrien Gardère won the international competition to design the Swedish Pavilion of the future world exhibition Expo 2020 Dubai. Built around Sweden's chosen theme of "co-creation for innovation", our proposal is based on the concept of the forest. As a Swedish emblem, an archetypal environment, a retreat place that stimulates imagination and creativity, the forest is the metaphor and perfect example of a dynamic, creative and interconnected ecosystem. The pavilion itself becomes a spectacular spokesperson for Swedish identity.
properties.credits_photo: Alessandro Ripellino Arkitekter, Studio Adrien Gardère & Luigi Pardo Architetti

properties.nom_etablissement: Pablo Reinoso Studio, Busan Infinity Line, LCT The Sharp, Haeundae-Beach, Busan, South Korea
properties.adresse: LCT The Sharp, Haeundae-Beach, Busan, South Korea
properties.description_projet: Entitled Busan Infinity Line, the work he made for LCT belongs to the series of «Garabatos» born after that of «Spaghettis Benches» and which, like the latter, sees the slats of the benches continue like lianas, as if they continue to grow within the framework in which they fit. With its 100 meters long and its 25 tons of stone, Busan Infinity Line is the largest work done to date by Pablo Reinoso. It is also the first for which it combines metal and stone, a Burgundy stone from the same quarry as that from which the feet of the Eiffel Tower were extracted. The association of these two materials takes even more meaning in Korea since it can recall, for example, the use of stone by Lee Ufan and the development of the line and the spiral by Lee Bae. With the stone very present in Asian culture and the lines in space that can evoke calligraphy, the work has undeniably oriental connotations It integrates even more into its environment as it takes up the curves of the building in front of which it is installed. And above all, installed facing the sea, it recalls the movement, the undulation, the endless surge of the waves. Like its lines that could never stop and continue their life. Life lines in short.

properties.nom_etablissement: Pierre-Yves Rochon, Atelier Joel Robuchon - Le Jardinier Miami, 151 NE 41st St STE 235, Miami, FL 33137, États-Unis
properties.titre_affiche: Atelier Joel Robuchon - Le Jardinier Miami
properties.adresse: 151 NE 41st St STE 235, Miami, FL 33137, États-Unis
properties.description_projet: The restaurant was designed by award-winning French architect Pierre-Yves Rochon, and includes a outdoor dining patio surrounded with plenty of plants. The space features black and white marble walls and floors, tall windows, marble tables, metal chairs, and a vertical garden serving as a focal point on the back wall. A 17-seat black marble bar sits off to the side with circular accent lights behind the glass shelving, and an illuminated spiral staircase that leads up to the second-floor L’Atelier Joel Robuchon.

properties.nom_etablissement: Gilles & Boissier, Mandarin Oriental Ritz (Madrid), Plaza de la Lealtad, 5, 28014 Madrid, Espagne
properties.adresse: Plaza de la Lealtad, 5, 28014 Madrid, Espagne
properties.description_projet: A French classicism tinged with the colors of the Spanish Golden Age, a reminder of the cultural influence of the Spanish Catholic monarchy in Europe. The selection of fabrics was made in the continuity of these themes We find the chiaroscuro of Velasquez, the golden ornaments of the great Spaniards, the pleated fabrics perfectly mastered, translated by one of the masters of universal painting. One feels the paintings of Greco staggering of beauty by their luminous colors, free, powerful, modern. According to Charlotte Chastel-Rousseau: "...very elaborate with bold colors - acid yellows, intense pinks, aniseed greens, electric blues, which often stand out on dark gray backgrounds"...Colors that seem even more daring today than they were in their century. We can see the rebellious freedom of a Goya before the Academy, who expresses his ideas on artistic creation, moving away from neoclassical precepts to affirm the need for freedom of the painter, who should not be subject to narrow rules. According to him, "oppression, the slavish obligation to make everyone study and follow the same path is an obstacle for young people who practice such a difficult art. "It is a true declaration of principles in the service of originality, of the will to give free rein to invention. Goya anticipates contemporary painting and various avant-garde movements of the twentieth century. Finally, we touch on Picasso who revolutionized his art, founder of cubism and companion of surrealism ..... It was necessary to give back to this hotel all its magnificence... the splendor of the golden century, the elegance of a royal bearing, the spirit of Spanish conquest, the glittering, gleaming and structured boleros, the damasks and golds, the enveloping draperies that come to warm you up, the travel trunks, the Cordoba leather, the reassuring classical codes tinged with modernity so as not to freeze in time. The Ritz is all this at once. An elegant and discreet conqueror, powerful in its restraint.

properties.nom_etablissement: Moinard Bétaille, JW Marriott Hotel (Seoul), 176, Sinbanpo-ro, Seocho-gu, Séoul 06546 République de Corée
properties.adresse: 176, Sinbanpo-ro, Seocho-gu, Séoul 06546 République de Corée
properties.description_projet: Bruno Moinard and Claire Bétaille have completely restructured the JW Marriott in Seoul, a large atrium from the 1980s. We now enter into what could be the evocation of a temple, a large volume 14 metres high and clad in wood supported by majestic pillars. The wooden slatted backdrop hides the passageways at the back and reveals kinetic effects. The scenographic lighting designed punctuates a journey of works of art including a large necklace by Jean-Michel Othoniel.

properties.nom_etablissement: AW², Banyan Tree AlUla, Al Ula, Al-Ula, Arabie saoudite, 43545
properties.description_projet: ACCOR - BANYAN TREE Luxury resort: 82 high-end villas (35 renovated existing villas + extension of 47 new villas), spa, gastronomic restaurants / ACCOR - BANYAN TREE Nestled deep within the vast desert of northwest Arabia, AlUla is known as a cultural oasis and living museum with more than 200,000 years of human history. Ashar is one of the project sites selected by the Royal Commission of AlUla (RCU) to develop the county into a word class tourist destination. Accor, under the Banyan Tree brand, will operate the expanded Ashar Resort with 47 new high-end units added bringing the total number up to 82. Designed by AW², these high-end villas will be complemented by the integration of a luxury spa and several gourmet restaurants. This will be guided by a sensitive design that allows each villa to blend discreetly into the striking natural scenery of the Ashar valley, located 15km from the Kingdom's first UNESCO World Heritage Site, Hegra.Our concept involves harnessing the natural beauty of the landscape with a project that seamlessly integrates into the site. It is a reflection of the 'intelligence of the site' - a design that is adapted and adaptable to the cultural, historical and natural specificities of Ashar. To understand this exceptional place, the guest experience is primordial. From the grandest scale to the smallest scale, from the public to the private, we are creating an experience which drives new emotions: perception, involvement, understanding. We study the ways the guests will grasp the site in its enormity, the emotions this will generate. Our project helps to shape the guest experience by creating a destination that responds to the journey of discovery that every visitor embarks on upon their arrival in AlUla. In this way the resort shall stand as an exemplar for the wider area’s future development. It shall be known as a unique destination combining a luxury experiential resort, heritage and culture.

properties.nom_etablissement: ciguë, NY Loft, Grand Street, SoHo, New York City
properties.adresse: Grand Street, SoHo, New York City
properties.description_projet: Residential loft conversion for a family in SoHo, New York. Materials : solid oak reclaimed wood floor, poured concrete, existing brick wall (white finish), ribbed glass, black powder coated steel, solid oak, lacquered mdf, D-tile system ceramics

properties.nom_etablissement: Atelier YOKYOK, The River Book, Jiaxing, Zhejiang, China
properties.description_projet: The River Book is an installation designed for the city of Jiaxing. This artwork is a volumetric interpretation of the geography and the history of the city. The map of the 9 rivers, taken as a starting point, is raised in the air and merged to the ground. It results in a dancing swirl appealing the visitor to come closer. The materiality of the object consists in overlapping different layers of transparent screens made of tense elastic ropes. These wide waving strips evoke the silk and textile industry heritage of Jiaxing. As getting closer the visitor can experience the installation in multiple sensitive ways (the sight, the touch, the hearing). One can enter and penetrate the hidden spaces within the installation and disapear progressively. Various openings let the visitor find their way through the pages, as an exploration throughout Jiaxing’s history.

properties.nom_etablissement: Atelier du Pont, SonBlanc Farmhouse Menorca, Alaior, 07730, Baléares, Espagne
properties.description_projet: Sonblanc hosts a unique space for those in pursuit of an authentic lifestyle. It is a self-sufficient and sustainable hotel which will offer its guests a unique experience by immersing them in the surrounding natural and cultivated landscape, almost to the point of total independence. The local marese stone is staged to create a setting that is natural and essential. Successful implementation of know-how while respecting traditions and the environment.

properties.nom_etablissement: COLLECTIONAL, Gallery COLLECTIONAL, 41st St - Al Satwa - Dubai - Émirats arabes unis
properties.adresse: 41st St - Al Satwa - Dubai - Émirats arabes unis

properties.nom_etablissement: studio razavi architecture, Boqueria Fulton Market, 807 WEST FULTON MARKET, CHICAGO, IL 60607
properties.description_projet: Once a design has contributed defining a brand, growth poses an interesting challenge for architects. How does one convey an established identity and familiarity of brand while refraining from copy pasting previous designs over to a new location? Boqueria in Chicago is located in the West Loop, in the former industrial & meatpacking neighborhood of Fulton-Randolf District which is being currently gentrified. Most buildings, new & old, have retained an industrial look: large open floor plates with columns. Because these spaces are predominantly horizontal in proportion, our approach was to layer the information so the design in its totality would provide a clear understanding of how it is organized. Prevailing materials are wood and black tiles, both not only reminiscent of the original Boqueria but also because of the feelings associated with them. One taking on a nice patina over time, the other providing a feeling of permanence & protection throughout the space. All light fixtures have been custom designed to create a variety of lighting atmospheres but also as a reminder of the eclecticism of Boqueria.

properties.nom_etablissement: Aurelien Chen, Dragon Mountain Pavillon, Rizhao, Shandong, Chine
properties.description_projet: An installation by Aurelien Chen recreating an ethereal and abstract version of a traditional Chinese landscape. Above all else, this installation is a landmark placed by the roadside to draw the attention to the entrance of the Dragon Mountain Natural site (Zhulong Shan), a typical example of « Shanshui » traditional Chinese landscape composed by mountains, forest, clouds and water. There are three different sequences of approach and just as many levels of perception in this installation. While approaching the site from the street, a vibrant mountain composed by 200 inox poles subtly appears in the distance. With speed, the poles become a single surface and the effects created by the different materials composing the poles reveal the shape of a new mountain. While the visitor moves closer, he discovers a miniature landscape in which he can move and stroll. The poles become a forest;a black marble river invites the visitor to walk towards the real mountain standing out against the horizon. The canopies placed above the visitor’s head to represent clouds, turn out to be mirrors. In this peaceful setting, urban life goes on reflecting itself on the mirror canopies and on the surface of the poles. The perforations on the mirror panels create an interplay of light and shadow marking the passing of time. At night, thousands of stars appear on the poles, perforated randomly, and give shape to a mountain vibrant with light. Overall planning : Urban and rural planning and design institute of CSCEC Design support : Zhou ZhiPeng (parametric design), Zhijian workshop

properties.nom_etablissement: Naço Architectures, Blossom Hill, Chine, Zhejiang, Hangzhou, Xihu, 天目山路518号 邮政编码: 3100234
properties.adresse: Chine, Zhejiang, Hangzhou, Xihu, 天目山路518号 邮政编码: 3100234
properties.description_projet: This semi-urban resort in located in a small village in eastern China. It aims to be a short holiday destination for young Chinese workers who wish to return to "Chinese-style happiness" and true human nature. The building is mostly composed of local recycled materials. Its small scale allows it to fit in its natural environment and to offer a stunning setting. It offers several various guesthouses and villas, restaurants, and a spa.

properties.nom_etablissement: Atelier Déambulons, Newtree Café, 4, Place du Luxembourg, 1050 Région de Bruxelles, Belgique
properties.adresse: 4, Place du Luxembourg, 1050 Région de Bruxelles, Belgique
properties.description_projet: Creation of two twisted trees and a bamboo canopy to decorate New Tree Café Bruxelles. In the center of the town, on Luxembourg square, this new cafe is a part of many other New Tree cafés, places where you can enjoy delicious hot drinks and its famous chocolate; This project, in collaboration with We want more, is a back to basics as the founder is Belgian.

properties.nom_etablissement: Jouin Manku, Blue By Alain Ducasse, Unit L101, 1st Floor, ICONLUXE ICONSIAM Shopping Centre, Klongtonsai, Khlong San, Bangkok 10600, Thaïlande
properties.adresse: Unit L101, 1st Floor, ICONLUXE ICONSIAM Shopping Centre, Klongtonsai, Khlong San, Bangkok 10600, Thaïlande
properties.description_projet: Blue by Alain Ducasse, designed by Jouin Manku, draws guests in to a world apart from the heat and intensity of Bangkok, offering an experience that plays on what is quintessentially French in the global imagination with a sensibility that avoids clichés and speaks too to the spectacular riverside setting of Thailand’s great bustling city. From the welcoming enclosure of the wood panelled foyer, guests pass in to the restaurant’s lounge, a space of seclusion and privacy inspired by the intimate gardens, the bosquets, of the Château de Versailles. Light from above and from the encircling wall of suspended walnut and brass lamps creates the effect of the magical dappled light of fireflies. Drawn further still the guests begin to glimpse the restaurant beyond – the sparkle and texture of the pleated chandelier, the luxurious royal blue of the walls and the floors – and then the glorious expanse of the floor-toceiling views across the city.

properties.nom_etablissement: Atelier Cedric Breisacher, Scales table, Galerie Philia, Bruxelles
properties.description_projet: Scales is a three-meter table made up of a single wooden top. Technically, the platform is held underneath with crossbars to prevent any future twisting. They were embedded inside the latter. The feet are turned and screwed to the top. The whole is sculpted by the movement of the body on the material, thus creating an organic form giving the impression of being in motion. The top is tinted with different vegetable stains to bring out the natural colors of the wood.

properties.nom_etablissement: Studio Catoir, Penthouse Munich, 81679 München, Deutschland
properties.description_projet: A couple living between Germany and the US commissioned Paris based interior design team Studio Catoir to plan their 150 m2 home in Munich on top of a three-story building including surrounding terrace. For their new Munich home they wanted light, open spaces in soft colours and materials. Meticulous craftsmanship brought Studio Catoir‘s and the owner‘s vision of a sensory, airy and colourful interior to life, using individually sourced marble and onyx blocks along with delicately coloured glass, mirrors and wood works.The result is an appealing combination of strict minimalism and feminine colours.

properties.nom_etablissement: Isabelle Stanislas, Casa Mahala Essence, Comporta, Portugal
properties.description_projet: A land of pinewoods and sand . . . a blank canvas to create a space to live freely, have fun, meditate, and spend time together. I envisaged this “House of Love” in the form of a square, open to its natural setting with long glazed passageways leading to the individual cabins housing the suites. Each one has its own secret garden, inside and outside. A haven of light and shade that toys with sunlight in a pared-down game of elegance and line. Sculpted with logs or timber frames, wood creates stripes in the white lime walls. Smooth concrete unites the floors, baths, and banquette seating covered with linen and cotton, as one. A world of earth and dune tones, fashioned out of natural mate- rials and with furniture made to measure. The sky inspired the color of the ceramic tiles lining the swimming pool, and conifers add to the comfort of the extra-wide sofas. An invitation to refocus on the essentials.

properties.nom_etablissement: Studio Idaë, Interstellar, Japon
properties.description_projet: Astronomical phenomenons have a direct impact on our environnement. “Interstellar” confronts the scientific representation to the real world by challenging scales and volumes. Eclipse, seasons, tides, the world we know is transforming with these phenomenons and it invites us to understand how our universe works.

properties.nom_etablissement: emmanuelle moureaux architecture + design, Universe Of Words, 3331 Arts Chiyoda (Tokyo), 6-11-14 Sotokanda, Chiyoda-Ku,Tokyo (JAPAN)
properties.description_projet: July 7th is the 100th year anniversary of the beloved Japanese drink Calpis. Coinciding with the Japanese star festival, Tanabata, Emmanuelle unveiled two installations, “Universe of Words” and “100 message bottles”, presented at the “Calpis 100th year anniversary, Let`s Meet at Tanabata” exhibition. On Tanabata day, Japanese people write their hopes and dreams on colored pieces of paper and hang them on a bamboo branch in hopes that their wishes will come true. Emmanuelle reimagines this tradition by extracting the sense of Tanabata onto the floating words. She chose the simplest written alphabet children first learn “hiragana”, composed of 46 different characters. In Tanabata, hiragana are used to express the hopes and dreams. The universe created by these floating hiraganas evokes an emotion through its stillness and its endlessness. By condensing the essence of the word itself, it derives to the emotion. The swaying hiragana form and symbolize the wishful colored pieces of paper swaying from the bamboo branch. The installation was composed of approximately 140,000 hiraganas, regularly aligned in three dimensional grids. Visitors could wonder inside the colorful space filled with hiraganas to share the sense of stillness. Sections of the installation were removed, creating paths that cut through the installation. Walking through the countless numbers of hiraganas, words gradually come to mind…As part of Emmanuelle’s "100 colors" installation series, the layers of hiraganas were colored in 100 shades of colors, creating a colorful Universe of Words. Within those characters, CALPIS bottles figures were lost and could be found along with the CALPIS logo, adding playfulness to the installation.

properties.nom_etablissement: A+A Cooren, Tiss-Tiss, 4 Albemarle Street, W1S 4GA London, Angleterre
properties.description_projet: Each work exposes a relief of fabric on the surface and sewn stitch imprints on the edges which are cast in aluminium. They capture a moment in time during which the linen fabric was carefully laid out and emphasize the beauty of traditional hand-weaving techniques and resulting irregularity. The fluid impression of the textile imprint is juxtaposed to the architectonic, self-supporting structure of the rigid aluminium plates.

properties.nom_etablissement: Charles Zana, Pantogia, 10 & 12, Via della Pantogia 07021 Arzachena SS Italie
properties.adresse: 10 & 12, Via della Pantogia 07021 Arzachena SS Italie
properties.description_projet: For this vast villa in Sardinia located in Pantogia, Charles Zana designed a dialogue between the typical landscape of the Costa Esmeralda and the architecture. Local materials and colors create an atmosphere that is both authentic and modern. Surface: environ 640m2

properties.nom_etablissement: Frédéric Saulou, Transhumance, Via dei Pandolfini, 20, 50122 Firenze FI, Italie
properties.adresse: Via dei Pandolfini, 20, 50122 Firenze FI, Italie
properties.description_projet: Design of unique furniture and objects for hotel rooms of Numeroventi, an hotel and a contemporary Renaissance art hub situated in the historical five-hundred-year old Palazzo Galli Tassi, in the heart of Florence. This project was developed during the design residency organized by Galerie Philia at the palazzo Numeroventi on the theme of the Renaissance. In the aftermath of this unprecedented year, "Transhumances" residency turned to the Renaissance era, to the notion of rebirth following the Dark Ages and the artistic flourishing that ensued, drawing here an interesting parallel between the isolation and hardship experienced during the pandemic and the cultural awakening that subsequently emerged. The artists were invited to celebrate nature and drawing from the resources available in the region to transcribe the Renaissance. The hotel has acquired the creations produced during the residency for furnishing these rooms. Solar Alabaster lamp and Fragment centerpieces for the living room and office, Médicis mirror S and L for rooms"
properties.credits_photo: Daniel civetta et Maison Mouton Noir

properties.nom_etablissement: Robin Bourgeois design residency , Villa Albertine residences
properties.titre_affiche: Industry city + WantedDesign Int. Residency program
properties.description_projet: Reinventing artists’ residencies, Villa Albertine is creating a network for arts and ideas spanning France and the United States. It offers tailor-made residencies for global creators, thinkers and cultural professionals.

properties.nom_etablissement: Atelier de Ricou, Villa Albertine residences
properties.titre_affiche: Renovation of Villa Albertine's "Venetian Room" , New York
properties.description_projet: Atelier de Ricou has worked within the Villa Albertine in New York. One of their most emblematic achievements within the building is the restoration of the Venetian Room, a waiting room for visitors and a masterpiece of the New York Gilded Age. In need of a complete renovation, the room was dismantled in 1949 and updated in 1997. The studio also completed work on the rest of the Payne Whitney Mansion (now Villa Albertine), with the goal of matching the new decor with the distinct architecture of the building.

properties.nom_etablissement: Office Dariel Studio ID Real Office
properties.description_projet: The id.real creative studio commissioned designer Thomas Dariel from the multi-awarded Shanghai-based design studio Dariel Studio to work with the independent interior designer and id.real Managing Director Anouk de Lesparda. Their main challenge was to transform the industrial unit into a XXI century design studio while enhancing its 1930s-building structure and historical heritage.

properties.nom_etablissement: Restaurant/bar Dariel Studio Lady Bund Renovated
properties.description_projet: Known for providing upscale, eclectically creative Asian cuisine, Lady Bund restaurant and lounge was recently renovated into a luxurious and exclusive club hosted in the upscale Bund 22 building. Following their original collaboration with Thomas Dariel in 2014, the owners of Lady Bund were completely taken by the French designer’s tasteful, yet unconventional blending of both Chinese and French cultures in the restaurant’s design. Without hesitation, they invited him back for their latest renovation endeavour.

properties.nom_etablissement: Hotel Dariel Studio Nanxun Blossom Hill
properties.adresse: No.109, Nanxi Street, Nanxun town, Huzhou, Zhejiang, China
properties.description_projet: Qiushuli Blossom Hill is located in Nanxun, Huzhou also known as the “Hidden Book Town”. During earlier times in the Republic of China, another renowned building entitled ‘Hidden Book’ was built by the wealthiest person in Nanxun Town Liu Chenggan’s Jiayetang. In 1930, he built another villa and named it “Qiu Shu Li”. Dariel Studio carefully renovated this ancient building, taking intricate measures to ensure the preservation of its heritage. Inspired by the owner Liu Chenggan’s collecting book of achievements, Dariel Studio chose the design concept “Hidden” and used that sense of bewilderment to reveal the story of Nanxun and Qiushuli village. Hidden can be portrayed as Liu Chenggan’s achievements in collecting books, but also the subtle beauty of hiding in the gardens in South China Style, and modern desires of hiding in nature and getting rid of the pressure and worries of daily life.

properties.nom_etablissement: Hotel Dariel Studio Xi'An Blossom Hill
properties.adresse: No.90, West Furong Road, Xi'an, Shanxi, China
properties.description_projet: Xi’an Blossom Hill Boutique Hotel is located in Chang'an City, who boasts the reputation of "the ancient capital of thirteen Dynasties". The hotel is adjacent to the Lotus palace of the Tang Dynas-ty. As a royal garden that once showed the style of the glorious period of the Tang Dynasty, it is also a place where the royal nobles, literati and civilians gathered together to travel. Its cross-cultural richness, even after such a long time, still vibrates. With such unique and strong regional characteristics, Dariel Studio merges new trends and ancient charms and achieves to design a bridge through time, offering guests a pleasant journey back to the Tang Dynasty.

properties.nom_etablissement: Hotel Dariel Studio Ningbo Blossom Hill
properties.adresse: No.1518, East Huanhu Road, Ningbo, China Ningbo, Zhejiang, China
properties.description_projet: Ningbo Blossom Hill Boutique Hotel is located in Hanling village on the south bank of Dongqian Lake. Since ancient times, Hanling has been a transportation hub with flocked merchants and prosperous marketplace. In 1140, Shi Hao, the Prime Minister of the Southern Song Dynasty, passed by and wrote a poem: "The landscape of Siming Mountain is different from the rest of the world, and the scenery of the Dongqian Lake is particularly beautiful, inside which there is a village called Hanling filled with sounds of the fishing songs, woodcutting and axes". The bustling atmos-phere of that period is evident. Ningbo Blossom Hill Hotel grew out of a wood-structured shop building with a history of one hundred years.

properties.nom_etablissement: Private residence Dariel Studio Pudong Penthouse
properties.description_projet: The latest luxury residential project designed by Dariel Studio is located in Pudong World Trade Binjiang Garden. The prestigious location and surroundings attracts elites from all over the world. Thomas Dariel, as the founder and leading designer of Dariel Studio, welcomed the challenge and transformed the entire space into an artsy and sophisticated penthouse. The structure, materials and colours have all been carefully selected to ensure they work harmoniously together.

properties.nom_etablissement: Office Dariel Studio Wieden+Kennedy Shanghai Office
properties.description_projet: Wieden+Kennedy Shanghai, a creativity driven advertising agency, advocates design and innovation and has delivered cutting edge works for world well-known clients such as Nike, Heineken, AB-Inbev, Tiffany, Fiat and Momo since it was established in 2005. Thomas Dariel, the principal designer and founder of Dariel Studio worked with the creative director of Wieden+Kennedy Yang YEO and redesigned the entire space, and succeeded in creating an ideal working environment for the W+K team by combining existing features of the space itself with the required functionalities.

properties.nom_etablissement: Private residence Dariel Studio Shenzhen Penthouse
properties.description_projet: The Yinhu Lanshan residential compound is perfectly located in the heart of Shenzhen and nested in a beautifully landscaped garden. The design of its top floor luxury penthouse has been entrusted to Thomas Dariel, the well-known French Designer behind the Shanghai-based agency Dariel Studio.

properties.nom_etablissement: Private residence Dariel Studio Beijing Fantasy
properties.description_projet: The last on-to-date residential project designed by Dariel Studio is a truly modern fantasy. Located in the vibrant Sanlitun area, this 1500 sqm apartment features an extra-ordinary décor that pays homage to the client’s eccentric personality.

properties.nom_etablissement: Private residence Dariel Studio The Blue Penthouse
properties.description_projet: Crafting a functional yet attractive and unique home for a family is a tall order for any interior designer. Thomas Dariel took up the challenge. After several months of renovation and a complete face-lift, he drastically transformed the existing space into a spacious, modern and sophisticated penthouse.

properties.nom_etablissement: Private residence Dariel Studio Prime Fitness
properties.adresse: 102, Building 1, No.3 Fenyang Road, Shanghai, China
properties.description_projet: Prime Fitness is a newly opened VIP personal training studio located in the heart of the French Concession. Providing an elegant and comfortable environment, Prime is a uniquely balanced facility designed to provide ruthlessly effective training in a five star environment. Focusing on one-to-one customized training, Prime offers its members the best recipe for getting in and maintaining physical condition by combining its rigorous training methodologies with the best nutritional products in the market.

properties.nom_etablissement: Private residence Dariel Studio (Re)Mix Club
properties.adresse: Workers' Sports Complex N Rd, Chaoyang, Chine, 100027
properties.description_projet: Located within the Worker Stadium arena in the vibrant Sanlitun district, The Mix Club does not need to be introduced anymore. After hip-hop hit Beijing, this very popular dance club quickly threw its hat into the clubbing ring, becoming a well-known stop for worldwide hip-hop DJ and being considered since as the best party scene in Beijing. Dariel Studio has been commissioned to design and renovate this true local Institution, starting by the underground part of the nightclub - known by the inner circle ones as (Re)Mix.

properties.nom_etablissement: Fermob, Maxx Royal Hotel - Turquie
properties.description_projet: Baraka Architects. The project area is located in the town called Kiriş, in Kemer district of Antalya, Turkey. It has an area of 150.000 square meters and is almost like a boundary between the developed and natural areas, a doorstep into the nature. The hotel has 291 rooms in total: 133 suites of 100 square meters in the main building, 84 family suites of 185 square meters on the slopes, 59 laguna villas of 150, 250 and 310 square meters on the beach and 15 beach villas of 250, 350 and 450 square meters. There are 6 à la carte restaurants and 4 bars.

properties.nom_etablissement: Fermob, Parlement Européen
properties.description_projet: The Esplanade Solidarność 1980 – with the Agora Simone Veil at its centre – defines the European Parliament site in Brussels, connecting its buildings with the Place du Luxembourg, the Brussels-Luxembourg train station and Parc Léopold. It’s the ideal place to grab a sandwich, read a book, or even just soak up the atmosphere of the European Parliament enjoying Fermob furniture. The Agora Simone Veil is at the centre of the Esplanade Solidarność 1980 and offers an impressive architectural backdrop. It is a great place from which to admire the architecture of the European Parliament’s Altiero Spinelli, Willy Brandt and Joszef Antall buildings. All three are named after charismatic figures who played an important role in the construction of the European Union.

properties.nom_etablissement: Fermob, Stavros Niarchos Foundation Cultural Center
properties.description_projet: When architect Renzo Piano first visited the area where the SNFCC was to be built, he immediately realized that the link between the urban and the natural landscapes had been cut; that the coastal avenue had separated the neighborhood from the sea. Renzo Piano was inspired by the name of the local area (Kallithea, which literally means "beautiful view’’) and decided to give back to the local people the beautiful view towards the sea. This idea was implemented conceptually in the most simple and effective way by lifting one side of a piece of paper and showing the gradual rise of the land towards the sea.

properties.nom_etablissement: Fermob, Mercato Metropolitano
properties.adresse: St. Mark's Church, N Audley St, Mayfair, London W1K 6ZA, Royaume-Uni
properties.description_projet: St Mark’s Church, a Grade I-listed building, has been converted into a food market. Following its stunning restoration, the venue is a haven for foodies, bringing together independent growers and producers offering a range of sustainable, eco-friendly, delicious and creative options. The vaulted-crypt basement, meanwhile, plays host to events, cookery lessons and musical performances. The idea is to have a space where people can meet, learn and share.

Zak+Fox Showroom

properties.description_projet: Jouffre participated in the renovation of the Zak+Fox's showroom. In the showroom's main room, five pairs of curtains in Pentimento - Segreto fabric were handcrafted by Jouffre’s seamstresses. Behind each curtain, five Austrian roman filter the light into the room. In Zak’s office, Jouffre upholsterers have created the wall-upholstery.

properties.nom_etablissement: Town House In Greenwich Village By Ingrao
properties.titre_affiche: Town House In Greenwich Village By Ingrao
properties.description_projet: Recently, Ingrao delighted an art collector couple with the design for their 5-story townhouse in Greenwich Village. Jouffre is pleased to have been able to participate in this major project by creating two sublime green velvet sofas and a cream-coloured sofa in a woven loop from Chapas Textiles.The Jouffre craftsmen also created the master bedroom bed, as well as the wall-upholstery installed behind it in the room.

properties.nom_etablissement: Morrocan Villa
properties.description_projet: It is in the palm grove of Marrakech that the Alberto Pinto agency has set down its suitcases to enlarge and rethink the dream home of a couple who have fallen in love with Morocco. The company Scène d'Intérieur, which became Jouffre Maroc in 2020, contributed to this large-scale project by designing a number of creations for the Moroccan villa. The villa's pergola houses the outdoor dining room and is dressed in subtle buttercloth sails made by Jouffre artisans. The latter created the headboards of all the rooms of the villa, designed by Alberto Pinto. Jouffre upholsterers and seamstresses also manufactured all the blinds and curtains for the villa, the upholstered bed frames of the numerous bedrooms, several sofas and armchairs, as well as the seats and back cushions of the garden furniture.

properties.nom_etablissement: Sagaponack
properties.description_projet: Jouffre created a custom-made bench and headboard for the master bedroom of a house in Sagaponack, for a project by interior architect Carol Egan. The perimeter of the headboard is made of oak and then painted in a shade of white to recall the tones of the room. A concave part covered in leather using the technique of "gainage" is then inserted into this frame. Finally, for comfort, a third soft element upholstered in fabric is positioned in the centre. The white and light roman shades, which let daylight into the room, were also made by Jouffre seamstresses.

properties.nom_etablissement: Chalet In Andermatt
properties.description_projet: Pierre Yovanovitch tasked Jouffre with crafting all the sofas, banquettes, cushions and curtains for this apartment/chalet. The challenge for the interior designer: create a protective "cocoon". This very attractive project was published in the January 2016 issue of AD France and AD Germany.

properties.nom_etablissement: Baccarat Hotel
properties.description_projet: A unique association reunited French designers Gilles & Boissier and Jouffre on the prestigious first Baccarat Hotel in New York, to achieve the wall upholstery in the lobby lounge of the hotel. Everything started with an original idea: creating the effect of hundreds of pleats unveiling one after another all around the four walls of the lobby lounge of the brand new Baccarat Hotel in Manhattan, due to open soon right in front of the MoMA. The ateliers Jouffre took up the challenge offered by the designers Gilles & Boissier and went beyond the traditional techniques of wall covering. For months, from Lyon to New York, Jouffre design office developed, improved and perfected a new approach of wall upholstery.

properties.nom_etablissement: One 57 Apartment
properties.description_projet: Jouffre was given the opportunity to participate in their first project within the One57 tower, designed by French Architect Christian de Portzamparc. Positioned on the 63rd floor, New York-based designers Drake/Anderson conceived an apartment, trusting Jouffre to use all three of it’s savoir-faires in order to help realize their vision. The draperies department fabricated all the window treatments for the bedrooms in fabrics from Fadini Borghi, Sabina Fay Braxton and Lauren Hwang woven by Holland & Sherry. Jouffre’s installers also set up the wall-upholstery on the walls of the master bedroom. For the guest bedroom, the upholstery department constructed a beautiful bed in a Charles Schambourg woven leather.

properties.nom_etablissement: Nespresso
properties.description_projet: After a first experience in Vienna, Nespresso Café opens a new venue in London. A break in the city, to oneself, for the urban in a hurry and very demanding in a place intimate, comfortable, efficient, fast and always impeccable. A luxury parenthesis in a small space : Because the rush is a continuous flow, because the moment is short, because the space is reduced to the essential, it is necessary to optimize the space and to work the different postures of tasting. In the spirit of yachts where the cabin is reduced, or in the spirit of small Milanese cafes, the postures are multiple: sitting up, standing, facing the street, sitting low, in group, alone ... Everyone finds "his parenthesis to oneself ".

properties.adresse: 9668 Shennan Ave, Nantou Residential District, Nanshan, Shenzhen, Guangdong Province, Chine
properties.description_projet: Saguez & Partners helped Huawei, the world's second largest supplier of smartphones, create its first world flagship in Shenzhen. More than just a store, it’s a three-story, 1,300 m2 piece of relational architecture. The era of flashy, brand-centric flagships has passed. The game changers in today’s commerce are those who demonstrate the generosity and empathy to create inviting, feel-good spaces where every detail has been considered to provide service.

properties.nom_etablissement: Sao Paulo International Airport
properties.adresse: Rod. Hélio Smidt, s/n° - Aeroporto, Guarulhos – SP, 07190-100 – Brésil
properties.description_projet: Overhanging Sao Paulo International Airport’s runways, which accounts for one third of the air transport in Brasil, the Villa Gru welcomes the new nomads, business women and men, who spend more time in the airports than in the planes. As a huge 500 square-meters balcony and a 70 square meters terrace, it joins the modern conviniences of hospitality to the effectiveness of an office, to make advantage and enjoy the travellers’ time. Part lougne, part co-working, part business center, this « contemporary house » inside the airport offers a wide range of premium services, enhanced by Saguez & Partners design, in multi-uses espaces : relaxation, bathrooms, massages, dining-rooms and private rooms set up for meetings, products presentation or contracts signings, secretaryship… The architecture makes the outdoor light come through the indoor spaces. The acoustic, insulation and ergonomics work makes the place comfortable and quiet in the very busy airport. The raw materials, warm and selected in the area, cohabit with Brazilian artcraft and art work exhibition.

properties.nom_etablissement: Barcelone Glories
properties.description_projet: Located in the heart of a Barcelona’s new vibrant district, the renewal of the shopping and leisure center reflects the architectural dynamism and the artistict influence of the Spanish city. Open-air, the center mixes the mood of the street to the personalised services of a shopping center and its 150 retailers. Like a creative explosion, bringing natural light underground in 70 000 square meters, the design of Saguez & Partners incorporates the new uses and the new position of the urban furniture – such as benches, canopies and pergolas - as well as five art masterpieces by the Catalan artist Javier Mariscal. The agency worked on the world leader in commercial property’s first Fresh ! concept, El Mercat, an indoor food market, where the commerce becomes a place of discovery, exchanges and meetings.

properties.nom_etablissement: The Skygarden : Show Case Apartment
properties.description_projet: The complete interior design and decoration of a 275m² apartment near the Roppongi district in Tokyo. Located on the upper level of a residential building in a park, the theme of the "skygarden" arrived instantaneously to guide the choice of materials and finishes. The creation of a double height entry connects the entertaining areas with the sleeping quarters that are placed on an upper level. A large amber glass covered structure receives leaves that appear to fall from the sky. The glass piece hides the main stair. A pleated leather wall, a type of immense origami, provides an intricate textured backdrop. The combined living dining area gives onto a planted terrace. The materials and finishes in this area work in concert with the exterior foliage. The main bedroom also plays on the theme of an articulated wall surface that also serves as a headboard. Niches are created to reduce scale at the bed and support built in furniture elements.

properties.nom_etablissement: Kit's Dream
properties.description_projet: For Kit, it was important to arrive in a refreshing atmosphere that provided a respite from the Moroccan heat. She thus treated the floor of the entrance in blue “zelliges”, of different hues, in order to recall the sea between New York and Marrakech. Her living room was separated from the entrance by curtains in "Atlantic blue" fabric with green tiebacks. A double-door on the left repeated the motif of palm tree leaves and gave access to the bathroom with a double basin vanity in "Calacatta Luxuoso". To the left of the vanity she created a large bathtub recessed in a niche, and dominated by an arabesque inspired by Berber symbols. The room was the heart of her space. She imagined the lower part of the walls in a dried earth color. The upper part of the walls, would be treated in an arabesque “bas-relief”. The motif would originate from a frieze at a certain height on the wall. Gradually, the arabesque would fade to create a large drawing of peaks and valleys. She said she would center the room with a high four-poster bed. In addition to protecting her while she slept, this "master-piece" would be illuminated to provide a soft intimate light in the room. Here the zelliges of the floor recalled the traces left by her steps in the sands of the Sahara.

properties.nom_etablissement: Walking on Clouds
properties.description_projet: A private 800m² apartment on the 67th and 68th floors of the MahaNakon Tower in Bangkok. “Walking on the clouds" is the theme of this project. A very fluid and open layout with very few closed rooms (two bedrooms, a massage room and three bathrooms) all sparsely furnished allow uninterrupted views of Bangkok. Full height windows give the impression that the sky and the clouds traverse the interior spaces. Several sliding partitions and Chinese works from the 17th century complete this refined, light and elegant atmosphere. The two key moments in the apartment experience are a reception area with a sort of "bow window" cantilevered from the facade (see the view from the outside) and an eight meter high double volume from which one may enjoy the sunsets. Throughout the entire project the floor is covered with a blue-gray Chinese limestone. The floor mixes with the sky and clouds to give the impression of floating

properties.nom_etablissement: A Spirit of Place
properties.description_projet: The complete interior design and decoration of a 125m² apartment in the Toranomon district of Tokyo. A Spirit of Place is the concept that guides the forms and finishes which are used to a create an expression that references the location of the Toranomon Project while at the same time giving a new voice to certain traditional Japanese crafts. These two orientations blend together to create a kaleidoscope of dreamlike urban and cultural impressions. As a result different almost surrealistic narratives come together to make a living environment that is amusing and unique.

properties.nom_etablissement: AOC
properties.description_projet: AOC is a French official label identifying products whose growth, harvesting and processing are performed in the same geographical area, using a recognized traditional “savoir faire”. It is the combination of a physical and a sustainable biological environment with an eco-responsible human community that creates the specificity of product which merits the title of an appellation d’origine contrôlée.

properties.nom_etablissement: Atbara House for Louis Vuitton
properties.description_projet: The salon ( both from afar and detail shot ) was the challenging room as it was the first room to enter after the entrance hall. It was meant to display their most expensive bags as adjacent was the exotic skin fashion collec- tion. Singapore is known for its vegetation but we were not allowed to bring in tall trees so Asian topiaries were used. Gildas Berthelot sculptural bronze bench and side table as the organic touch vegetation, polyedre lantern by Hubert le Gall with gilded bookcage by Vicenzo de Cotiis for Ceccoti, Hubert le Gall petrified wood gueridon intermingle with Martino Gamper armchair and Gio Ponti stools. Introduction of furniture through a tropical cul- ture with Brazil through Martin Eisler chairs and Joaquim Tenreiro sofa and a handknotted wild silk carpet by Fort Street Studio produced in Nepal. You do not see the artwork in these photos but they were loaned from a collector that resonated instantaneously with the guests.

properties.nom_etablissement: The Bodrum Edition Hotel
properties.adresse: Dirmil Mahallesi, Balyek Caddesi No 5A Yalikavak Mugla 48990, 48 Bodrum, Turquie
properties.description_projet: The Bodrum EDITION is just steps from the bay, 3 kilometers from Yalikavak Marina at the western point of the Bodrum peninsula, and minutes from Bodrum Castle and Bodrum Amphitheatre. The boutique hotel features 108 guest rooms, suites and villas, most with views of the Aegean Sea — some with private pools, balconies, and gardens. Every room features custom-designed furnishings and indulgent marble bathrooms. Indulge yourself with treatments in the state-of-the-art spa, which includes a salon, Turkish Hammam, and fitness center. Relax through the afternoon in the Infinity pool and access to the exclusive beach club with a jetty that houses private cabanas. Innovative food and beverage outlets include 2 bars, a gourmet specialty grill overlooking the bay, a night club, and an all-day casual dining venue featuring Latin-American cuisine as well as more localized menu offerings. The resort also has over 12,900 sqft/1,200 sqm of indoor and outdoor meeting and event space including meeting studios, a ballroom, and boardroom.

properties.nom_etablissement: Hotel Sahrai
properties.adresse: Hôtel Sahrai, Dhar El Mehraz, 30 000، Fes, Maroc
properties.description_projet: The Hotel Sahrai is opening in Fez, Morocco. The five-star Hotel Sahrai, designed by the architect and designer Christophe Pillet, enjoys spectacular views of the largest medina in the Arab world, taking in twelve centuries of the city’s history in one fell swoop. Just 2h30 away from Paris, it offers a totally new hotel experience in Fez. An alternative to the shady isolation of the riads and the impersonal feel of the big resorts, its architecture on a human scale is a combination of tradition and contemporary style.

properties.nom_etablissement: Axis Tower
properties.description_projet: A new shopping center starts functioning in Axis Towers skyscraper, which has become another landmark in the center of Tbilisi. Axis Towers combines five development directions – 5 star Pullman Hotel, a business center, entertainment, residential and commercial spaces. In addition, there are exhibition and recreational spaces in the complex. First habitant of the ultramodern complex will be the popular hypermarket of agro products – “Agro-hub”, which opens on March 26. Its concept is to provide its customers with 100% healthy and natural products. The parties agreed to locate “Agro-hub” in Axis Towers a few months ago, based on memorandum, which was signed on August 9 of 2018. The hypermarket will occupy 2460 sq. meters of the commercial space of the complex.
